25 minutes Post injection: Left eye issues. Itchy, swollen behind the eye and feeling like something was in it or irritating it. It kept driving me to check if something was in it. I put in renu eye drops and did not think any more of it. 40 minutes post injection: both feet red and swollen left foot about half of the top, the whole right foot looked like a giant hive or welted area across the whole top of foot. The injection site began being quite sore, and it also looked welted and felt hot to the touch. I kept checking my left rib cage and my left thumb as I was sure there was going to be hives, because I could not stop rubbing or scratching them as they itched so badly. I continued itching and feeling weird tingly sensations and either rubbed or scratched these areas to no avail. Even my head itched terribly by the second day. 45 minutes post injection: Tightness and scratchiness in throat appeared and my throat was sore, my voice began going out and my voice got hoarse. There was about a two inch area of my throat in which I felt I needed to keep trying to clear something that was stuck. (This made no sense to me as I was able to drink water without any issues.) I had a slight cough every time I stopped drinking, so I continually drank water while I was not trying to sleep. My chest was tight, but because I have asthma I took albuterol and thought nothing of it. (This really did not help, but I did not get worse either.) About an hour after the shot, I constantly felt on the verge of shaking, much like when you have a fever, but I did not think to check my temperature until the following morning when I was extremely tired, felt like I had a sinus headache and possibly did have a fever. My temperature was 99.4 degrees farenheight. At this point, I felt very flu-ish and achy. My armpit area hurt a lot and I chewed two aspirin. I experienced wheeziness, chest tightness, and hoarseness the second and third day as well. I had the morning congestion and stuffiness as well as the need to keep clearing my voice still as of this morning but to much less degree as the initial onset. The skin itchiness is still ongoing, but to a much lesser degree than previously had.

Moderna COVID-19 vaccine EUA I had a fever of 101.2 by 3/3:30pm and then it was 102.0 by 4:30pm and sustained at that level until around 1am.  The fever was accompanied by chills that felt like the neuropathy you can have with Shingles - meaning my skin felt sensitive to the touch.  It was not like normal flu muscle aches.  My whole body felt like it was made of lead or concrete and I was just lethargic.  It is curious that in hind sight the chills were not accompanied by any sweating.  The chills and fever stopped about the same time (1am), but the fatigue carried on for a couple days.   Additionally, my left arm where I had the injection was very painful and my range of motion was limited by the pain for probably 36 hours.  72 hours later the muscle is still sore, but the range of motion is fine.   Further, on April 4th I experienced nausea  with the beginning of my period which is not a normal menstrual symptom for me to have and the nausea has continued on to April 5th.

3/22/21 Admission HPI: 71 y.o. male with a history of poorly controlled diabetes mellitus and COPD.  He presented to my office today acutely with a several day history of increasing shortness of breath.  He has increased his prednisone at home recently and been increasing the frequency of his DuoNebs.  Despite this, he states that his oxygen saturations have been staying in the low 80s.  He has a hard time walking due to the shortness of breath.  He states previous to about a week ago he was doing very well.  He denies any fever.  He denies any known exposure to coronavirus (COVID-19).  In the office today his oxygen saturations were 88% on 4 L. Because of his failure of outpatient therapy, he will be admitted to the hospital for further evaluation and treatment.  This patient has a history of severe respiratory decompensation that happens very quickly.  Therefore, it is medically urgent we get him into the hospital.     3/25/21 Admission HPI71 y.o. male with a known history of severe COPD and type 2 diabetes mellitus.  He came to my office with a several day history of increasing shortness of breath.  He had increased his oral steroids and breathing treatments at home and despite this was still having oxygen saturations in the low to mid 80s on 2-4 L of supplemental oxygen.  In my office he was extremely diminished and had basically failed outpatient therapy.  Therefore he was admitted to inpatient status for acute treatment of a severe COPD exacerbation requiring IV antibiotics and IV steroids.  He was admitted and treated with IV treatments.  He did recover nicely.  However, he was found to be extremely physically deconditioned.  Because of this he was thought to be an excellent candidate for swing bed and is being transitioned to swing bed.    4/5/21 ER Practitioner Note: Upon arrival to ED trauma room I found patient to be in cardiac arrest, CPR in progress. History is that EMS was called to the scene for a patient with chest pain.  Shortly after arrival at his home  patient developed a cardiac arrest.  They followed standard ACLS  protocol and the patient was intubated. Blood sugar normal. As CPR was given, medications were administered consisting of epinephrine and 1 mg in 2 different doses along with 1 amp of bicarb. IV access via an IO. Patient was then transported to the emergency department.  Upon arrival, CPR was continued and oxygen supplied via endotracheal tube with good tube placement verified by auscultation and good sat readings.  Monitor was placed and patient demonstrated initially a sinus rhythm but there was no pulse.  Therefore, diagnosis was PEA and no reversible causes were identified.  ACLS protocol was followed with epinephrine 1 mg IV every 5 min.  He received a total that including EMS, 5 mg of epinephrine and 1 amp of bicarb.  Monitor at this point revealed the rhythm changed to an agonal rhythm.  When CPR was given, there was good results from the CPR.  However, CPR discontinued and there is no pulse and patient had an agonal  rhythm for several minutes, pupils were fixed but not dilated year.  Lungs demonstrating clear bilateral breath sounds when he was bagged via the endotracheal tube.  No external signs of any trauma noted. The patient's sister is here and she is a registered nurse.  We had discussed management at this point with her and all were in agreement that the code be terminated.  At 1015, patient was pronounced deceased..    ACLS protocol was followed.  See nursing record for medication and vital sign details.   Code outcome: Deceased   CC time 20 minutes.

A husband and wife was called in to get vaccine originally scheduled for 9:15 am to get vaccine. The husband was 1st.  The wife, was second.  She was afraid of shots and did not want to see needle. I only had a 1 and one-half inch needle drawn. So I asked if she was ok with me drawing vaccine in front of her. She was ok. I got the 1 inch needle ready with separate syringe and drew up vaccine . I forgot to draw the vaccine because I went to give shot in left arm and vaccine plunger did not move. I looked at plunger, and it was at bottom. I realized my error. So I informed patient.  I did not put band-aid on at first as well. She did notice a drop of blood. So I placed a band-aid on her arm.  She was ok with me giving the shot in right arm at 10:15am .  She was ok.  Vaccine  is accounted for with no extra plus I'm very confident no vaccine was given in left arm.   I called her to see how she was doing.  She was fine and cheerful.  I also clarified her prescriber name to let them know.  I told he if she has any questions let us know.

On Friday, 4/2/21, a client (49 yr old male) arrived to the 30 minute Vaccine Recovery lot after COVID 19 Moderna Lot# 020B21A administration at 11:40am. Patient had reported history of rash after taking both Cipro and Penicillin. At 11:55 am while pt was being assessed by vaccine recovery lot, pt reported sudden onset of involuntary movements and mild shortness of breath. The EMT called for the Vaccine Recovery Lot Medical Lead. Began assessing patient at 11:57 am, noting the pt was having involuntary movements of the upper and lower extremities every few seconds. 12:00 pm BP 152/98, pulse 65. Patient was alert and oriented with normal skin color.  Pt reported feeling anxious and "maybe it is all in my head". Pt reported the blood pressure on scene was " higher than my normal at 120s/80s. Pt denied any history of recent illness or other vaccines. Pt stated, " I should have known something would happen, I had a premonition about this". Repeat vital signs at 12:32 pm BP 152/98 and pulse 65. Pt continued to have episodes of the involuntary upper and lower extremities lasting approx 3-5 minutes per episode. NP explained to pt that she could not allow him to drive with these movements and pt agreed to evaluation with EMS and transport to local ER for further evaluation. NP instructed to call for EMS. Call was made at 12:48pm and EMS/Fire arrived onsite shortly after. While awaiting Fire Department and EMS, pt reported to NP, "I have a history of Aspergers Syndrome". Also NP spoke with pt's spouse who also agreed pt should be evaluated at local ER. He was transported to the local hospital.
HISTORY: Pt reported history of Obstructive Sleep Apnea with CPAP use and  Aspergers Syndrome

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 4am the day after my first shot I woke up to swollen, blood shot eyes which were irritated and itchy. After an hour and a half the symptoms were not getting better so I decided to take claritin since it was similar to the allergic reaction I have to mold. An hour later my eyes were better but still sore around them. The next day they were completely better.   Also, since taking the vaccine I seem to forget things easily,  things that I put in the microwave are sitting there the next morning which is very unusual for me to be so forgetful so many times and even at work my focus was scattered and things that were routine were becoming challenging to remember to complete. After 2 weeks it seems to have faded, although once I became aware of what was happening I have made a conscious effort to remember things.  I realize that these may seem like small events,  but I feel that it is something that should be looked into as it was/is rather concerning since this was only my first shot and the second is supposed to react worse.  I am still contemplating whether getting a second shot is wise for me.

These symptoms developed very shortly after he received his first dose of the Moderna vaccine. He initially attributed these symptoms to side effects of the vaccine. When they persisted, however, he called his primary care physician who recommended that he seek evaluation. He was evaluated at an urgent care on 3/30 where he tested positive for COVID-19. His shortness of breath progressed, and he presented to the ED on 3/31 for evaluation. CTPE was negative for PE but did demonstrate viral pneumonia. Ambulatory pulse oximetry was negative for desaturation. He was discharged home. Since discharge, his symptoms have continued to progress. He was planned to receive monoclonal antibody earlier today, 4/2, however when he presented for his infusion he was found to be hypoxic to 89% and tachycardic to 130s. He was sent to the ED for evaluation. He continues to have diaphoresis and chills although believes his fever has improved. He has some chest tightness with deep inspiration. He otherwise denies unusual headache, sore throat, productive cough, chest pressure, abdominal pain, flank pain, dysuria, and diarrhea. He reports that his PE was provoked by obesity and a lengthy plane flight in 2017. He was on anticoagulation for 8 months and has since been off.  On arrival to ED, VS AF, HR 122, RR 30s, BP 120/90, SpO2 97% on RA. He was in significant respiratory distress and was therefore placed on HHFNC with improvement. VBG 7.42/39 and lactate 3.9. CMP w/ AST 40, ALT 40, AG 15. Serum creatinine elevated at 1.13 from baseline 1.0. CBC w/ WBC 5.6, HGB 17.7, PLT 257. HS troponin 10 -> 8. Given his hypoxemia and history of pulmonary embolism, CTPE was performed and negative for PE however did demonstrate bilateral consolidations consistent with COVID-19 viral pneumonia. Procalcitonin was negative. He was given dexamethasone. He was also given 500 mL LR with clearance of lactate. He was admitted to Hospital in stable condition.

This patient received his second Moderna vaccine at 12 days from his first dose instead of 28 days. This was due to an error in scheduling his appointment for his second dose as well as the pharmacist not verifying the timing of his previous dose.   I apologized that he had been vaccinated with his second dose early. He stated that he felt well "I'm all right" We attempted to share information about vaccine efficacy and side effects but he  interrupted us stating that "I'm all set" He had no questions for us and asked to get off the call. He presented as not concerned about side effects or efficacy and  seemed happy to be done with the 2 vaccine series.  Follow-up  offered phone contact info- he declined.  he stated he is seeing his PCP next  week.  QUESTIONS ADDRESSED IN THE DISCUSSION: none "I'm all right" "I'll continue to wear my mask"  CONTINUED COMMUNICATIONS REGARDING THE ADVERSE EVENT: Advised to seek care for any symptoms of concern.  For Primary Care and other care team members:  Per CDC no additional dose is needed in this situation.  Vaccine symptoms are not expected to be worse with early second dose  vaccination.  Efficacy data is not available for this situation but significant protection  from vaccination is expected.

Tinnitus began immediately following vaccine.  At nighttime when the surrounding noise is reduced and the quiet occurs, I now find it difficult to fall asleep because there is a continual loud buzzing/ringing noise running throughout my brain and extending through my ear canals.  I have never had Tinnitus and always pitied people that had the condition and never understood the issue, until now.  There should be a warning on these vaccines that they may cause Tinnitus.  In this instance, ignorance is not bliss because blissful sleep is no longer going to be allowed in a certain percentage of the population that receives these vaccines?  I intend to contact my doctor for testing. I am disappointed that no one in charge has brought this to the attention of the public.  We have the right to make factual decisions.  There are numerous people suffering from Tinnitus currently being ignored.  Given this condition, how can I take another vaccine knowing it could further exacerbate this problem.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 3:44pm, writer was paged to tend to patient who per monitor began having sudden hiccups. On writer's arrival to room, patient observed to have sudden onset abnormal breathing pattern and intermittent spasmodic hiccups. Writer called for additional assistance, oxygen and crash cart. Patient denied headache, dizziness, rash, throat discomfort, hoarseness, nausea, or chest pain. Patient was alert and verbal in between spasmodic hiccups with appropriate coloring; and she voiced that the active abnormal breathing happens when she gets an asthma attack. She simultaneously was reaching in her purse and worded "my pump".  Oxygen via NC at 2Lpm provided to patient. Patient self-administered 2 puffs of her Ventolin rescue inhaler, though observed patient's inability to hold breath adequately after each puff.  BP: 150/70 P: 98bpm RR: 22 Pulse oximetry 100% on 2LPM via NC. Dr. reached via telephone who ordered for patient to be sent out via 911 to hospital. Lungs and Heart auscultated by RN � no abnormal findings. At 3:55pm patient noted to have shallow rapid breathing, and voiced she felt lightheaded, weak and feeling a burning sensation in chest, and writer noted patient appeared to lose control over her head and neck. Patient repositioned to supine in recliner. Writer coached patient to control breathing with pursed-lip breathing technique and switched oxygen via NC to face mask, patient was able to follow commands well and remain alert.  Dr. ordered Diphenhydramine HCl 25mg IM STAT. RN administered Diphenhydramine HCl per order at 4:00pm to right deltoid without incident. EMS arrived and assumed care at 4:00pm. Patient transferred self from recliner to stretcher with EMS assist. Patient left facility via stretcher and 3 EMS attendants at approximately 4:15pm, verbally responsive and oriented x 4 without supplemental oxygen and in adequate control of her head and neck muscles. VS: 170/60 P: 88  O2 Sat: 100% on room air.
Patient death within 60 days of receiving the COVID vaccine series

The first Moderna Covid-19 dose was given to me on March 8, 2021. On the morning of March 31, 2021, three weeks and three days after receiving the immunization, I started developing a red rash on my abdomen and back which I noticed at 8am that morning. By noon that same day, the hives had started to spread to the rest of my chest, neck and arms. I called the dermatologist and received a 4pm appointment. By the time I got to the appointment, the rash had covered 75% of my skin. Much of the rash was red and much of it was raised, itchy hives. The dermatologist gave me a prescription for prednisone and I was told to also take benadryl or zyrtec for the itching. Within two to three days, the hives disappeared. The dermatologist told me to go ahead and get the second dose of the Moderna vaccine which I am doing at 5:15pm today, April 5, 2021.

I received my second Pfizer vaccine at about 8:05 Friday morning.  The first 12 hours post second shot were uneventful. Then, much like my first shot, the pain in my shoulder started to drastically intensify.  Around hour 13, I started to get chills. Intense chills that lasted throughout that night. I had a temperature between 100 and 101. Chills, sweating, and slept fitfully, up and down all throughout the night.  Then I woke up the (Saturday) morning after my second dose, and I began to have very intense stomach cramping that was very debilitating. It felt like an awful kind of heartburn. The chills are gone. I still had pain in my shoulder. I was curled up in a ball, then stretching out my body, just trying really to not be in intense, intense pain. Finally, beginning around 1:30 PM on Saturday the pain started to very slowly lessen.   By about 5 PM I could say the stomach cramping/heartburn kind of pain was almost fully gone.  I woke up on Easter Sunday feeling still like my shoulder hurt, but all the other very very intense pain and symptoms seem to be almost entirely gone ? Well, except the headache that I really hadn?t cared much about while my stomach was cramping. But the headache had been present all day Saturday as well.   Saturday and all day Sunday, I had but one of my girlfriends describes as a ?hangover headache.?  I would say it?s something like when you have a couple glasses of wine where the tannins don?t agree with you. That lasted all this two days.   Sunday evening my shoulder pain started to increase and really really started affecting the muscle connecting my neck to my shoulder, I think it?s called the trapezius. As it intensified, I started feeling numbness in my fingers as we were trying to rub it away. I?ve had really bad knots in that muscle in the past, so the numbness didn?t scare me. The muscles in my left arm continued to cramp and just really hurt. All the way from my trapezius and the side of my neck on that side down through my bicep. And when I say cramping muscles and feeling like they?re knotted, the only way I can think to describe it is to say that they were SCREAMING.   I tried everything I could think of, but nothing helped. Finally I used an ice pack which worked for about 20 to 30 minutes and then I used a heating pad which also worked but not for very long. At this point I was just hoping I could sleep.  Around 12:30 AM, I was finally able to somewhat drift to sleep after getting in a manageable position, I guess. I woke up every hour or two in screaming muscle pain. And I woke up for good just before 6 AM today, Monday.   I've been at work today with strong, but not debilitating, pain in the muscles in my left arm and returned, more mild, heartburn pain in my stomach.

Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  First day after getting the shot I got a feeling of being very tired throughout the day I did not feel like to do anything. Also my arm was very very sore. Even moving it slightly a bit would hurt. At the reporting time, the outcome of vaccination complication was not provided.  On unspecified dates between 2020 or 2021, the patient was vaccinated with the first dose of SARS-CoV-2 spike protein mRNA vaccine (reported as PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE). On 04-MAR-2021, the patient had severe side effects of vaccine including seizure disorder and right arm swelling. Her husband brought her to the hospital, and she was admitted. On an unspecified date (reported as today), the patient was scheduled for second dose of the vaccine, but she was scared to go, as it affected her mental status.   The causal relationship between vaccination complication and measles, mumps, and rubella (wistar ra 27-3) virus vaccine, live (M-M-R II) was related.

She did not contact her primary care physician about her concerns because she doesn't really go to the doctor. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Passed out; Dehydrated; kept vomiting; Chills; her arm was swollen, itching and caused pain; arm was swollen; caused pain; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer,  concerning a 69-years-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced arm was swollen (peripheral swelling), itching (pruritus), and caused pain (pain in extremity), passed out (loss of consciousness), kept vomiting (vomiting), chills and was dehydrated (dehydration).  The patient's medical history was not provided.  Concomitant medications reported included ascorbic acid/biotin/dl-alpha tocopheryl acetate, nadolol, acetylsalicylic acid, sertraline, levothyroxine sodium and spironolactone.   On 13 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: 030M20A) intramuscularly in the left deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.    On 13 Feb 2021, the patient's arm was swollen, itching and caused pain for about 2 days. On 14 Feb 2021, the passed out. The patient stated that she did not know how long she was out and that the event did not happen again. Since 14 Feb 2021, the patient kept vomiting where she couldn't eat or drink at all and she could eat on 20 Feb 2021. On 14 Feb 2021, the patient had the chills and was dehydrated which lasted for 7 days. The patients' doctor told her not to get the second Moderna COVID-19 vaccination.  Treatment information was not provided.    The patient was advised by her doctor to avoid getting the second dose of mRNA-1273.  The outcome of the events, arm was swollen, itching and caused pain, were considered resolved on 15 Feb 2021. The event, passed out, was considered resolved on 14 Feb 2021. The outcome of the  events, kept vomiting and could not eat or drink at all, were considered resolved on 20 Feb 2021. Food tasted bad--my stomach was sour. I was lethargic and slept most of Sunday and straight through Sunday night/Monday morning. My nose and cheeks pealed this (Monday) morning and I look as if I have a mild suntan. I haven't been in the sun or wind for more than a few minutes, for over a week and I haven't been outside at all since I received my vaccine.   The soreness in my arm is now only at the vaccination spot and it is tender only if I press it; touching it no longer causes wincing.  I feel flushed but no llonger have a fever. I'm no longer taking Ibuprofen. Food is tasting better today but it's not back to normal--my stomach is still a little sour.

Vaccine #1:  Only the sore arm as described on the Fact Sheet. Vaccine #2:  Stabbing anterior, posterior, and lateral left thorax chest pain at approx. 3 hours post injection lasting 2-5 seconds. Cardiac arrhythmias at 10 hours post injection:  I could feel the arrhythmias as they were about to start with fullness in my throat. Unable to detect radial pulse during episodes and no cardiac beats heard on auscultation.   Complete compensatory pause noted per palpation and auscultation.   Frequency of about two (2) episodes every 30-45 minutes for approximately three (3) hours, with gradual decrease in frequency over 24 hours.  By 24 hours post to present  none noted.  During all of these episodes I was supine. At 72 hours post the axillary swelling and chest pain (not the same size as the stabbing pain)  noted at 36 hours post had decreased from a full football in size to approx 1/2 a football.  Captured a picture of that (the half-size football), but not the full-size event. Considerable abdominal pain to LLQ at approx 90-100 hours post vaccine #2 that persisted for 24+ hours.

On the 5th day after my vaccine, I first experienced a very itchy, red warm lump on the back of my left leg (just above my knee, but, on the back of my leg). And then a day later, a 2nd itchy, red warm lump appeared very close to the 1st lump. They each lasted a day or two.  They were very irritating...very honestly, they would wake me up at night due to itchiness. And then on the 8th day after my vaccine, my left arm (near my injection site) started looking exactly the same...however, it was terribly red...as well as itchy and very hot to the touch; the redness started small, but then grew over the course of the next day, and spread below my elbow (I would estimate 7 inches or so).  It was horrible. I iced it all day long. It was terribly uncomfortable...it made my whole body feel warm and uncomfortable. I went to the doctor for something unrelated, and the nurse mentioned that she had a similar experience (and also had the Moderna vaccine)...otherwise, I would not have pieced it all together. By the 10th day, all 3 of the lumps were gone. To be honest, I dread my 2nd vaccine (this week) due to the discomfort that the lumps caused.
LAB_DATA: None. I applied some steroid cream, and antihistamine cream to try to reduce the swelling and itchiness; I'm not sure it made much of a difference, though.

The body aches continued, was having joint swollen in wrist, knees and shoulders, and fever continued to 103 throughout the day and wavered from 101 to 103. She then took 2 qadvvils at 6:00 PM.  On the 17th she became very dizzy, had chest heaviness, legs were very heavy to the point not aqble to lift them or walk.  Her heart rate remained in the 140.  at 8:00 PM she had fever of 102.9.  The next day still dizzy, off balance, still had the stabbing muscle and flank pain.  She was still tachycardia fever still at 101.  That same day she checked her VS, her SATs were 96%.   The light headedness continued and 2 syncopal episodes on that Saturday but recovered from that.  She then Sunday had the light headaches, had trouble walking and by Monday she started feeling a lot better, and little by little the symptoms continued to improve.  Now she feels completely better, the swelling and pain is gone, she can walk again.   These symptoms were similar to when she had the COVID virus.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Every single side effect on the sheet - began with muscle soreness about 2 hours after the shot, which lasted about 1 week.  Around 2:30am the morning after the shot, I was awakened from a deep sleep by chills and sweats, which lasted for about 36 hours from that moment. These were moderate to severe, such that these symptoms alone would have prevented me from making it through the workday. However, things got worse. Due to chills and sweats, I took my temperate, which was about 99F at that time. Over the course of the next 10 hours the temperature spiked to 100.4F oral.  I tried to go back to sleep at 2:30am, but I could only toss and turn due to the chills. Perhaps due to lack of sleep, perhaps due to vaccine, I developed a head ache  and some nausea - both of these are extremely rare symptoms for me, as I rarely have a headache more than once a year. By 5am, with climbing temp, sore arm, headache, upset stomach, chills, sweats, muscle aches and exhaustion, I consulted my boss - a 20 yr clinical pharmacist - who advised me this would end after 24 hours. Therefore, I took no meds and waited it out.  Soon after 12:30pm, when the fever reached 100.4F, I felt the temperature break. It was almost 24hrs to the moment, and after that the symptoms began rapidly resolving. The temperature subsided completely by about 7pm that evening. Chills and sweats the next morning. Some fleeting headache and nausea the following day. A lot of dizziness and faintness over the next week or so, which I am unsure about - but it could be some sort of backup/accumulation of high dose Mg for my back, in the presence of the vaccine and/or immune response.  I say below that I visited the doctor because, if my boss were not a clinical pharmacist, I would absolutely have made a doctor's appointment.  Because I get COVID19 tested at work, I had no need to make an MD appt.  I got COVID tested, and I consulted with a clinical COVID19 expert - better than a doctor's visit given how long it takes to get in to see my PCP and how little he knows about COVID19  vaccine responses.
LAB_DATA: Only the temperature, which I took using oral route, home thermometer.
OTHER_MEDS: Metagenics Inflavanoid Intensive  Care 2capsBID Metagenics Myocalm Plus 2tabsBID

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came in to the pharmacy to receive second dose of the covid-19 vaccine around 1230pm on 4-2-2021. She received the vaccine around 1:00pm from a pharmacy tech, and within 5ish minutes told my tech that her jaw line was tingling and her lips felt swollen.  Pharmacist on duty, took the e-kit and went to check on her.  She seemed to be talking fine and stated she wasn't having a hard time breathing.  Pharmacist made the decision with the patient's consent to call 911 to be on the safe side.  No meds were administered.  Paramedics showed up, evaluated patient, and with the patient's consent, took her to the ER.   The pharmacy followed up with the patient on 4-5-2021 to make sure she was okay.  She said she was doing fine and that on 4-2-2021 her throat started to get prickly when she got to the ER so they administered bendadryl which helped.
ALLERGIES: sulfa drugs, muscle relaxers, nsaids, seasonal

I am writing to you in regards my Moderna adverse reaction. I got your information from a small Facebook group that?s going through the same issues as me. On 1/31/21, I received my first shot of Moderna. I was told to stay 30min because I have a Sulfa allergy. I also received a flu shot 3 weeks prior. After 15 min I started to feel tingling in my face and throat tightness. As time passed, I started to feel like I couldn?t breathe at one point. As I continued to have issues breathing and started getting nauseous and lightheaded, they informed a nurse to look over me. The nurse had a student nurse do my vitals manually. She gives out standard numbers 60 heart rate and 120/80 blood pressure. My normal blood pressure is elevated in 130-140/80-90. I had to be picked up due to feeling unwell. I went home took Tylenol and slept.  The next few weeks I kept feeling zaps of sharp pain in my chest area. On the 12th day after the vaccine, I had a panic attack. The panic attack started with a sharp pain in my neck and when I inhaled it hurt. I got heart palpitations and again felt like I couldn?t breathe. I never suffered from a panic attack, so we called 911. The EMTs came my blood pressure was 200s/100s and elevated heart rate (sorry don?t remember exact numbers). It was suggested I go to the ER since my numbers were high. In the ER I told the doctor about my vaccine incident. They got blood work done and she decided to do a CT scan and X-ray since something was elevated ( I don?t remember what was elevated. I am working on getting that info). My EKG, CT scan and X-ray all came out fine. I was then diagnosed with panic disorder. I was sent home and after a few hours I started to feel an internal tremor.  I describe the tremor as having a cell phone on vibrate its usually is in my lower abdomen to pelvic area. My blood pressure kept spiking up into 180-190/80-100. I kept reaching out for help by going to ER once more, 3 urgent care visits and my primary. No one could help me, and I kept getting labeled as having panic/anxiety disordered. My primary doctor said I could be having adverse reaction to the vaccine, but I just have to wait it out. The internal tremor I feel constantly and sometimes it?s in my chest. I have muscle twitching, tingling in my lower limbs, muscle pain, and blood pressure spikes. I do feel like my symptoms cause anxiety because ill have these spells where I feel adrenaline running through me which will cause anxiousness. My blood pressure is getting better, but I still have spikes and have had another panic attack.  I have been on Lexapro 5mg and gabapentin 300mg 3x a day for 5 weeks. During that time, my symptoms have not improved. I will be getting off the medication soon. I never had any of these issues prior. I don?t drink, smoke or do any drugs besides the medication prescribed.   On 3/30/21, I reached out to my psychiatrist again and went into more detail about everything and she said she believes me about the vaccine side effects.  She recommended I go back to my primary care doctor and ask to be referred to UCSD covid long haulers study to see if they can help me. I wanted to share my information to see if it might be help to your research.  Thank you for your time
LAB_DATA: Just the treatment stated above. I haven?t been referred to any specialist yet.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Today we gave epinephrine to a patient and called 911. COVID-19 Vaccine Moderna 1st dose:  Lot # 030B21A  Called on radio at approximately 1:15pm from "elbow" in the road at the top of the lower parking lot outside of fenced area asking for clinical lead. Worker responded on radio. They said patient returning after receiving vaccine one hour ago and concerned she is having allergic reaction. Worker asked if patient needed 911 call and worker responded she was not sure. I grabbed the golf cart and the worker got our NP. I drove us to the corner. We arrived there 1:16pm.  Patient was in passenger seat of car. Spanish speaking only. Translation by myself and a family member. Patient reported receiving Moderna vaccine approximately 1 hour ago and now experiencing throat closing up and chest tightness. Her voice was very hoarse, almost a whisper. She appeared to have difficulty breathing. Noted use of accesory muscles and high respiratory rate. Breath sounds clear, no wheezing (checked by NP). She also reported history of allergic reactions and use of epinephrine pen.  I called 911 within first minute of arriving on scene. Also announced to city on radio that ambulance arriving to please clear traffic.  Epinephrine 0.3mg IM administered at approximately 1:20pm in right anterior lateral thigh by NP. Patient tolerated well. Reported feeling better within 1 min of Epinephrine administration. Visibly calmer. Respirations less labored and rate appeared within normal limits.  Ambulance arrived very shortly after epinephrine administration, in approximately 3 minutes. Patient was assisted to gurney and brought into ambulance. She was taken to the Hospital. The ambulance left at 1:28pm.
ALLERGIES: History of allergic reaction and epi-pen use, but unspecified

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received First Dose Moderna lot #030B21A  Patient vaccinated without incident and sent to observation lot., RN in the observation lot greeted patient on arrival. Patient stated she was feeling "weird and a little dizzy" Jonetta had her recline her seat and open her window for air. She reported worsening dizziness and called APP (who happened to be very close).  APP arrived to car and asked for observation / emergency supply cart. Found patient reclined in passenger seat c/o feeling weird and dizzy. APP noted increased respiratory rate and patient said she felt faint. She then slumped in seat and appeared to lose consciousness for a few seconds. She was breathing although breathing appeared mildly labored. She opened her eyes after a few seconds and began to shiver significantly. Pre-epinephrine assessment by APP: BP WNL, tachycardia and elevated respiratory rate. Skin cold. No wheezes.  APP administered 0.3mg of epinephrine IM at 1237 to right thigh through jeans. Patient tolerated well. Vital signs post epinephrine showed an initially high BP and heart rate and then returned to within normal limits 5-10 minutes later. Patient feeling much better after epinephrine.  I was assigned clinical site lead, I arrived on scene 3-4 minutes after APP. I called 911 and ambulance arrived within 3-4 minutes. Patient did not want to go to hospital but agreed to get in ambulance for 12 lead EKG and vital signs, all of which were stable. Patient refused hospital. Husband drove her home at approximately 1:30pm.  APP called MD on call, they called patient at approximately 2:30pm and reported to APP that she was at home with no further symptoms

I also had diarrhea and nausea, but same reasoning. By Saturday I was really noticing the lightheadedness/faintness, especially on standing. I would have to lean for a minute against something on standing and felt like I was going to black out. I was also sleepy and low energy, but had trouble falling asleep. Sunday was bad as well and I had insomnia again, though the diarrhea cleared up by then. Today, Monday, I feel poorly, but I think it is chronic illness poorly and no longer vaccine side effect poorly (I am sleep deprived too). I have only experienced some lightheadedness on standing today and fatigue/sleepiness that may or may not be usual for me. I am putting down that I've recovered because that is my best guess

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 53 y/o woman presented for her first COVID vaccine. She had hx of allergic reaction to IV Contrast in 2006 and 2014 - within minutes of receiving IV contrast for an imaging study she developed throat closing, difficulty breathing and vomiting. She has tolerated vaccinations and IV medications in the past without any problem. She also tolerated bowel prep for her colonoscopy a few years ago. Denies known allergy to PEG. I sent secure chat to her PCP and received approval to proceed with vaccination today.  The patient was warned of the increased risk of allergic reaction to the COVID vaccine due to her allergic reaction to IV Contrast in the past. She expressed understanding and stated she still wanted to receive the vaccine despite the increased risk.   10 min after receiving the vaccine she developed significant nausea and dry heaving. Vitals were within normal limits. Physical exam was unremarkable except for anxiety and vomiting.  18 min after the vaccine she developed lightheadedness and a headache. 27 min after the vaccine she developed diaphoresis and a sore throat. Vitals and physical exam were monitored closely.  30 min after the vaccine she developed itching of her ears, nose and posterior pharynx. She also c/o burning sensation from her nasal passage to her throat. She had coughing and throat clearing. Vitals were unremarkable. Exam revealed increased distress.  35 min after the vaccine she suddenly developed tightness of her throat associated with worsening throat itching and difficulty breathing.  Vitals: HR 110, Spo2 94%, BP 136/80, RR 20 PE: A&Ox4, appears anxious and is in acute distress, she had hands around her throat.  Cardio: tachycardic rate, regular rhythm, radial pulse 2+ Pulm: Tachypnea noted, lungs clear to auscultation, no wheezing, cap refill < 2 sec Skin: facial flushing noted, diaphoresis resolved, no urticaria, no swelling or erythema at injection site.  Expressed to patient that I was concerned about an allergic reaction occurring and described my next steps of administering EPI and calling EMS. She was agreeable.  EMS was called by CMA. Epi Autoinjector 0.3 mg injected into RIGHT upper outer thigh at 10:57 AM Her throat tightness, throat/ear/nasal itching, throat clearing, cough, lightheadedness and headache all resolved within 10 min after the EPI was given.  Oral benadryl 25 mg was given.   EMS arrived at 11:18 AM and took over care. The patient was agreeable to be transferred to ER for further monitoring.
LAB_DATA: No lab or medical tests were completed here at the Vaccine Clinic. She was taken to the ER via EMS. Unable to see ER notes.

Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA - Dose 2 Beginning 8 hours after shot (adverse reaction to first dose began 12 hours after shot), headache, fever, chills, fatigue, terrible all-over body aches, joint pain. Within 24 hours, developed rash on arm near injection site, with blisters and itching, followed by all-over body itching - but no rash other than on arm. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient received her FIRST dose of Moderna COVID vaccine on 1/26/21 and SECOND dose on 2/23/21. On 3/8, she first started to experience shortness of breath, which was attributable to cardiac etiology and diastolic heart failure at the time, but which in retrospect may have been her earliest symptom of new onset myasthenia gravis, which is the AE I am wanting to report. She was hospitalized from 3/8-3/13, and underwent extensive cardiac workup that was negative. She again developed shortness of breath on 3/17/21 and was re-admitted to the hospital on 3/18/21 for diuresis for presumed diastolic heart failure exacerbation, received diuresis from 3/18-3/22/21 but then developed new onset diplopia, at which pint I evaluated her in neurological consultation on 3/22. Her brain MRI disclosed an UNrelated incidental  small left cerebellar infract, but her neurological exam showed a new R lateral rectus palsy and new moderate to severe left eyelid ptosis, suspicious for myasthenia gravis. Anti-acetylcholineseterase antibodies--- binding, blocking, and modulating, were all sent off and came back all strongly positive on 3/26-27/21. The patient then called stating she had developed recurrent shortness of breath, new onset dysphagia, and worsening double vision. I urgently re-evaluated her in outpatient follow-up in my office on 4/2/21 and sent her immediately to the hospital to be readmitted, where she remains as of this reporting date and she has been receiving IVIG with improvement in her symptoms. She did NOT have any previous known history of eyelid ptosis, dysphagia, diplopia, or muscle weakness. In retrospect, the patient states that her current symptomatology began around 3/7/21 with the benefit of hindsight. I am reporting this event because it is very unusual for an 82 year old WOMAN to develop new onset of myasthenia gravis, and it is a known autoimmune disease, and a vaccine would be a plausible trigger for its development, or trigger for its first symptomatic manifestation. I was also especially concerned because my fellow neurologist, ALSO had a patient develop myasthenia gravis about 2 weeks or so following their second dose of the Pfizer COVID vaccine. It would be an EXTRAORDINARY coincidence for two instances of new onset myasthenia gravis to occur 2 weeks post- vaccination at essentially the same time in an institution of our size, so we both felt obliged to report both cases ASAP to the VAERS. I was not able to reach the patient in her hospital room today to get additional specifics about where she got the vaccine, its lot number etc., however she is a retired and has indicated her willingness to provide you with any and all additional information you need, and I am also personally very willing to provide any additional information about her eventual outcome.

2 Days after receiving my 2nd Pfizer shot, I began to have blurred vision in only my right eye.  For the first week, it began to get worse a little bit each day making it difficult for me to see out of my right eye.  By the end of the first week (February 22 - February 28), my eye sight had gotten so blurred/darkened with my vision in my right eye that I was uncomfortable operating a vehicle.  During the week of March 1 - March 7, I did not drive and went to the  Eye Institute on March 1st assuming it was a retinal tear or something more serious due to the lack of vision in one eye.  There was blurred vision with a darkness that covered the center part of my eyesight.  It was very difficult to see if it was bright outside and there were little floaters here and there.  I explained this to the urgent care doctor at Eye Institute and they completed retinal scans and various other tests/scans.  The doctor did not see anything physically wrong with the eye.  For that next week (March 1 - March 7), my vision continued to remain exactly the same where there was a large, dark spot constantly when I looked out of my right eye.  As I stated above, it was also very sensitive to light.  I went on Monday, March 8th to get a second opinion, but they also could not tell me what was wrong.  Exactly 2 weeks after the vision issue started, my vision began to return normally.  During the week of March 8th, my right eye regain its vision back to its normal eyesight.  By the end of the week (March 13th-ish), I would say my vision was at least 75% back to normal.  It is 100% back to normal now and has been for a few weeks now.
LAB_DATA: I went to  Eye Institute and they completed a retinal scan and various other scans that showed zero concerns/issues.  There wasn't a retinal tear, no breakage, no cut, nothing.  I went to  receive a second opinion and they also did not find anything wrong with my retina/eye.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was unable to get email thorough to local health department and felt I should report to someone. I did not see a physician or dentist (was trying to wait a day or two in case it was in response to the vaccine), but reaction in the mouth seemed unusual to me so I wanted to report. I do not use vsafe, smartphones pointing to codes but felt like I needed to alert someone about unusual reactions to my second Merderna vaccine. My first vaccine was on 2/26/2021 at #013AZ1A. I only had a slight sore arm. No other symptoms. My second vaccine #028AZ1A on 3/26/2021 had severe reactions. On 3/27/2021 I had a sore throat, sore arm, migraine, but the scary thing was I developed severe swelling in my mouth. Gums where wisdom teeth had been extracted years ago had two huge abscesses. My gums were there were gaps in my teeth were swollen and coming up between my teeth. My mouth was sore and sensitive. I couldn't even bite down on jello. On the third day I began using Orajel and gargling in warm salt water. By the 4th day my mouth was back to normal but I have sensitivity in lower and upper right teeth but improving daily. I am able to bite, chew and see no swelling. I had no problems with my teeth prior to the vaccine. Migraine disappeared after two days. I did not take tynol. It was as though the vaccine was trying to attack what it might have thought to be a problem in my mouth. (Only able to sip warm broth for two days). Very scary.
ALLERGIES: pencellian, motrin, advil, ibrophfen, glucafouge, shellfish

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Monday, April 5, 2021    Thank you for this opportunity to share my experience. Healthy, no underlying conditions, active, On Saturday, March 27th at around noon, I had my 2nd Pfizer vaccine, administered in my right arm at the  The injection was painless, I had zero symptoms initially following the injection and none the rest of that day.  On Sunday, upon waking, my arm was uncomfortable but not painful. No symptoms on Sunday.  On Monday, upon waking, my arm was more uncomfortable, I felt a little off; minor headache, minor light headed feeling, so I took 2 Tylenol.   On Tuesday, upon waking, my arm was very painful at the injection site. It was difficult to raise my arm above my shoulder.  I did not take any Tylenol although I still felt a little off. I massaged the injection site. We have a brand new 2021 hot tub that we use daily so I got in and positioned my right arm injection site on a bubbly jet to massage the area. It helped alleviate the severe pain and muscle stiffness.   I had an English muffin, 1 poached egg and banana, I showered, got dressed and my husband and I went to the bank and to store. While in store, around 12:30 ? 1:00 PM, I began to feel light headed, very hot; not a fever hot, just very temperature hot. I told my husband I needed to leave NOW. He got me a cold water and we left.   Upon arriving home ? say 20 minutes later, I was very light headed and nauseous. I went directly to bed to lie down.  By 2:00 PM, my nausea was extreme as I laid in bed. I knew I would feel better if I could throw up, but I also knew I would have to make my self do it because it wasn?t happening on it?s own.  I went to the bathroom and began to put my finger near my mouth and that?s all it took and I violently vomited 3 times.  The vomit was liquidy, and old blood red. Remember, for breakfast I had had a dry English muffin, poached egg and banana. NOTHING red!  I screamed for my husband who came in and was shocked to see the color and volume of vomit. He helped to clean me up and help me back to bed, where I immediately returned to the bathroom with severe diarrhea?the same old blood red color.  Again, he helped to clean me up and help me to lie down.  He got me cool water which I sipped.  Within an hour, I rushed back to the bathroom and VIOLENTLY threw up again. Severe convulsions, unable to breath in between each convulsion.  Old blood red, liquid, and to make matters even worse, the same color liquidy diarrhea. This went on for another 20 minutes.  My husband was with me the entire time as the extreme convulsions contorted me and I could not keep aim to the toilet. I thought I had internal bleeding and was dying! I have never been this sick!!!  Again, he cleaned me up, helped me back to bed where I was exhausted. He encouraged me to sip cool water which I did.  On Wednesday morning upon waking, I was less nauseous. My husband urged me to try a dry English muffin (my normal morning routine). I was able to eat a few bites and keep them down. I showered to clean myself up and that did me in. I made it to the couch for the day. Sipping water and trying to complete the dry English muffin. On Wednesday I did not have a bowel movement.  On Thursday morning upon waking, I was less nauseous and was able to drink a cup of tea and finish a dry English muffin. On Thursday I did not have a bowel movement.  On Friday morning upon waking, I was not nauseous. I was able to drink a cup of tea and finish a dry English muffin and 1 poached egg. On Friday I did not have a bowel movement.  On Saturday, now 1 week following the injection, I was better. Able to shower, able to eat, able to get out of the house. I had a small bowel movement that was the same dark color but somewhat in tact.  On Sunday, Easter, I felt really good. Ate breakfast, lunch and dinner. Had a better bowel movement; not dark but ?my? normal color and condition.  My theory (and I am not a scientist or medical person in ANY way!!!). When my arm was SO painful at the injection site and I got in the hot tub and placed my arm on a bubbly jet, it?s like I released the full burst of vaccine ? like a bolus ? into my system, rather than letting the muscle spasm release allowing the vaccine to gently circulate through my body.  In July and I can assure you that in my all of my years of owning this body, I have NEVER experienced any flu or sickness with this severe or this violent convulsing vomiting and NEVER experienced the color of the contents!!!!  My husband, with no underlying conditions, has also had both of his shots. He had no side effects. Yeah!!  Since this experience, I have not been able to drink coffee or wine, of which both were a regular part of my diet.   Now on a lighter note, less coffee and wine isn?t a bad thing, however since this episode I cannot fathom the thought of either of those entering my system.  Thank you again for this opportunity to share my experience. I am glad to have both shots and I hope I am NEVER this sick again!!!!

This morning the pain in arm and joints has gone down but is still there; this is the first morning I woke without a fever  but low grade fever returned this afternoon as did the redness in my face & headaches.

Pharmacy prepares all Covid-19 vaccines in syringes.   Pharmacy performs an inventory count at the beginning and the end of clinic to reconcile the number of doses dispensed/administered and the # of unopened vials that remain.  At the end of clinic on 3/31/21 when pharmacy was reconciling the vials remaining it was noted that there was an extra vial of Pfizer Covid Vaccine that did not reconcile with the # of doses dispensed and administered.  After investigating it was discovered that a Pfizer vaccine vial was used/reconstituted twice.  Therefore it was determined that of 98 patients, 6 patients received normal saline instead of Pfizer Covid Vaccine. This included 90 second doses and 8 first doses. It is not possible to know which of the 98 individuals received the vaccine or normal saline.  After consultation with the Department of Health and the CDC's Vaccine task force, it was determined that the best course of action is to offer all 98 vaccinee's the option to repeat the vaccine dose.   We will be offering vaccinee's an additional dose of Pfizer or J&J/Janssen at an interval of 21 and 28 days, respectively.  This is being done by direct notification of the patients via phone call describing the error and the optional recommendation for repeating the dose. Providers of the patients have been notified. All vaccinees will be informed of the potential of  experiencing more pronounced side effects with an additional dose. For patients who decide to receive the extra dose, the previous dose will be removed from the Registry.   The root cause analysis of this event revealed that the incident was related to a pharmacist not discarding a used vaccine vial as soon as it was used.  Pharmacy implemented corrective action plan, which included reeducation to all preparing vaccine and new measure to assure pairing of one vaccine vial with one normal saline vial for each set of 6 doses prepared and discarding used vials as soon as the preparation and checking process is complete.

He experienced slur, facial droop and left side hand weekness. We called the paramedics right away and they checked him and took him to the nearest Emergency Hospital. They ran tests, did CT scan and diagnosed him with Ischemic Stroke on his right side which has effect on the left side of his body for facial droop and weekness and not being able to get up. He was threated with Mechanical Thromboctomy to remove the blood clot. He stayed in the hospital for 8 days and is bed bound up until now and is transferred to a re-hab. He still can't stand. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient received the Janssen Covid 19 vaccine (lot 1805022) on 3/17/21. Today (4/5/21) the patient called to report several adverse reactions. She stated that she had body aches and chills the day after the vaccine. The aches went away but the patient reports that the chills in her hands, legs, and feet have persisted. The patient also said that she started to have facial paralysis on 4/3/21. Also on 4/3/21 she reported developing multiple skin rashes on different areas of the body. She also said she went to the ER and had multiple tests run, including an MRI to rule out stroke. She did report to her primary care doctor who advised her to see a Neurologist. I offered to reach out to her primary care but she did not provide the information. I advised the patient that she would need to seek care from a provider who could assess and treat her as needed. I called Janssen and they said the facial paralysis is a very rare possibility but did not have any additional information to provide me. They advised me to tell the patient to seek medical care as necessary. I spoke with the patient multiple times this evening and provided her with the information to VAERS and Vsafe. I also let her know that I contacted Janssen and gave her the information they gave me. I expressed to her that I understood that she was concerned and she could reach out to me if needed. I also will follow up with her later in the week.

I had nearly 2 weeks of spiking fevers of about 99-100. The fever spikes would last between 5 and 10 minutes. I know these were not "hot flashes" because I am long past that and am on controlled HRT. 7. The newest side effect is frequent brain fog. I have spoken with a nurse in my doctor's office and she stated that nobody else she has spoken to has had any of these side effects. Patient presented for COVID vaccine and indicated that she has had anaphylaxis but only to allergy shots in the past, not to other vaccines. Our immunizing technician gave the patient her first COVID vaccine between 2:45 and 3pm. She sat down for observation with her daughter beside her. About 10 to 15 minutes later the patient began coughing more and more profusely. She expressed chest tightness and became flush in her face and upper chest. She stated she was going to use her EpiPen that she carried with her. An in-date EpiPen from the pharmacy was provided instead and the patient self-injected in the right thigh as she was familiar with its use. She was monitored after and she continued to cough along with having some jittery feelings from the EpiPen. This continued for about 3 minutes with her still straining to cough. She wanted to hold off on the second dose of the EpiPen as she was still jittery but the paramedics were called for her. The paramedics arrived and they took over the scene and took her to the emergency room at 3:25pm.
PRIOR_VAX: Patient stated she had anaphylaxis or difficulty breathing from allergy shots in the past.
ALLERGIES: NKDA - only listed reactions to allergy shots specifically

I received the vaccination on 3/25. On 3/26 and 3/27 I experienced vaccination site soreness, which began to dissipate on 3/28. On 3/29 and 3/30 I experienced a persistent headache and also newly appearing red splotches at the injection site that went away within 48 hours. Then, on 3/30 I also began to experience extreme fatigue and felt "foggy," which persisted on 3/31. During the night of 3/31-morning of 4/1, I woke up multiple times during the night alternating between hot flashes and cold sweats and feeling slightly short of breath, and my eyes were very bloodshot upon fully awakening. I recorded a temperature of 99.9 degrees F the morning of 4/1 and still felt fatigued, so I called off of work and slept most of the day. By the evening of 4/1 I felt entirely better, as if nothing had happened. I want to note that I was diagnosed with a mild case of COVID-19 during early December 2020, so I wanted to submit my vaccination experience in case you are disaggregating side effect data by whether or not patients have previously had COVID-19. Of course I cannot be sure that my symptoms were definitively related to the vaccine, but if they were then the duration of symptoms seems quite lengthy.
OTHER_MEDS: Oral birth control pills, vitamin B12, vitamin D, oral probiotic pill

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 30 minutes of first dose of vaccine reported fever/sweaty, higher blood pressure and lightheadedness. Went to the clinic and confirmed through nurse triage that fever and blood pressure were elevated.   Blood pressure ~128/86 Patient's normal range is 90/60 Fever was 99  Next three days: On and off fever that never went above 99. Patient has chills, and normal symptoms when having a 99 degree fever.  For the next 10 days continued to have elevated blood pressure (123-128/80), lightheadedness and vertigo. Blood pressure, lightheadedness and vertigo  continued even when patient is laying down. Stronger adverse effects included numbness, leg pain and chest pain that felt like a heart attack, especially whenever bending leg at the knee.  Symptoms remained constant and did not lessen over the 10 days. On the 11th day adverse effects drastically reduced though blood pressure was still higher than normal but closer to normal range.

A bit worried about taking the second does this friday given the chest pain and blood pressure issues after the first dose.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  Second dose of Pfizer vaccine received Friday afternoon (4/2/2021). Went to bed Friday evening with "normal" side effects of mild fever and sore arm at injection site. Woke up Saturday morning with no sense of smell or taste. Called primary care provider who conducted a video visit and expressed concern that he may have had an asymptomatic case of COVID-19 prior to injection (no symptoms displayed at all in weeks prior). Order a COVID test for Sunday morning. Woke up Sunday morning with sense of taste and smell back. Proceeded with PCR test, which came back as "negative" on Sunday evening. No other symptoms observed, and other side effects noted above (sore arm, fever) resolved by Sunday morning as well. Seems to suggest loss of sense of taste and smell likely due to vaccine since there was a clear temporal relationship which resolved in approximately 24 hours.

Doctors continue to learn more about the coronavirus as they study the lasting effects it can have on people. COVID toes and fingers in one of them. It's not a very common or dangerous complication, but it? s caused by inflammation to the blood vessels in your fingers or toes, and it's directly linked to the virus. "Ironically people who have a mild case of COVID are getting this unusual complication and some of them have had weeks or months for that to clear up, said Dr. .Many doctors have been calling this unusual complication 'COVID toes' or 'COVID fingers.'  "Basically it's a funny reaction to the infection, where you have actually an exaggerated or a strong immune response, Dr. said. It's being seen more in healthy individuals who don't have a severe case of the coronavirus. Dr. suggests seeing your doctor if you are experiencing these symptoms. "So because you have damage to the vessels, fluid just leaks and causes local swelling and the redness,? he said.

I had surgery for spinal stenosis on 07/09/2020, including a decompression and fusion at L4/L5.  I reported the following symptoms, which I attribute to the COVID-19 vaccination, to my spine surgeon.  I had my second dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on Monday, March 29th at 5:45 PM.   Lower back pain in the general area of my surgery (07/09/2020) woke me up from sleep around 4:30 AM Tuesday (03/30/2021) morning.  Being woken up from sleep had never happened previously - not before surgery, following surgery, ever.  I recall the pain being a dull throbbing ache, nothing sharp.   I recall being generally pain free Tuesday during the day and went for a mile and half walk Tuesday evening and hit  about 20 40-yard (or less pitch shots) Tuesday evening.   I woke up Wednesday at my usual 6:45 AM.  Although I don't recall being in pain getting out of bed, I do remember being in excruciating pain the remainder of the day.  It hurt to walk (landing either foot) and the only position that I had any relief was sitting at work.  The pain was frequent, sharp, and up to a 6 on a scale of 1 to 10.  I felt exhausted and feel asleep at 7:30 PM Wednesday night.   I was in significantly less pain Thursday, although it was still uncomfortable rising from a seated position and bending at the waist (to assume a putting position in the office) caused pain to the extent that I chose not to fully bend.  Thursday night was generally OK but there was one point, while seated on a couch, where I felt a sharp stabbing pain in the general area of my surgery.  I tried to change positions to alleviate the pain, but it persisted for 30 seconds before finally subsiding.  The pain felt like I was being stabbed and it was a 8 or 9 on a 1 to 10 scale.   Friday was a repeat of Thursday.  Generally, I have very little pain except when I stand from a seated position (1 or 2 on a 10 point scale) or bend slightly at the waist (3 or 4).  The pain is dull but the pain from bending does prevent me from bending comfortably.   All of this pain is new this week since Monday.  This past weekend I worked in the yard, including some heavy lifting and digging.   Is there any chance this is a side effect of the vaccine?  Should I schedule an office visit to evaluate the pain?  NOTE:  I was generally symptom free by Saturday, 04/03/2021 and totally symptom free by 04/05/2021.

The morning of April 3, staff at the Clinic discovered a discrepancy in the preparation of Pfizer vaccine doses. It was discovered that several undiluted vaccine doses were administered. Staff accounted for all unused undiluted vaccine doses. Unfortunately, 10 undiluted vaccine doses had been administered to patients and were not able to be retrieved. This patient received one of the undiluted doses.   The medical team contacted the CDC to determine the potential side effects and observation requirements of receiving an undiluted vaccine. The CDC confirmed that the recipients of the undiluted doses may experience stronger side effects and symptoms than someone who received the diluted dose (sore arm, flu-like symptoms, etc.).  The site public health officer spoke with suspected recipients of the undiluted vaccine to explain potential medical side effects. District will follow up to monitor their status.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Five days following vaccine #2, pt presented to the emergency department on 3/2/21 with complaint of severe generalized arthralgias and fatigue. 5/25 Received vaccine at 9:30 a.m. at the hospital. Sore arm developed about 3 hours later. Later that afternoon, had muscle aches and tiredness. 5/26 10:30 a.m. noticed a couple hives on my upper thigh and inside forearms. Realized they were there before I got to work, but didn't make note of it.  12:00 felt very tired, muscle aches, especially in neck, felt like mild flu. noticed hives/rash getting worse in the afternoon. They were not itchy. 8:00 p.m. Called on call doctor due to worsening rash/hives. "Breathing seemed fine. Dr. called back and advised 10 ml Benedryl along with nightly Zyrtec. Took 10 ml liquid Benedryl.  9:00 p.m. noticed breathing got a little easier, less constricted. Made sure my son's epi pen was available if needed.  Saturday, March 27 Had chills in the middle of the night, turned on electric mattress pad to get warm, making hives worse. 4:00 a.m. 10 ml Benedryl. Didn't notice breathing getting better, or not lasting very long. Contemplated ER if got worse. 8:45 a.m. 10 ml Benedryl. Temp is 98.8 10:00 took Zyrtec and ibuprofen Called Dr. in the morning, who suggested medrol dose pack of steroids. Due to past history with hives, requested 10 day course of steroids. 11:00 6 prednisone 1:30 p.m. 10 ml Benedryl possible less internal agitation 5:45 Benedryl 11:00 p.m. Zyrtec, temp 98.2. Hives continued to spread, but at much slower rate. Felt on face, ears and back of head. More prickly sensation form the hives. Some spots so many hives it is just one large red spot. Felt very hot. Tried to use ice pack to cool down and ease tingling irritation from hives. Sunday, March 28 1:10 a.m. Benedryl for restlessness (especially in legs), chamomile tea 4:00 a.m. magnesium, which finally settled the restless legs. 11:30 prednisone Called Dr. back since hives didn't seem to be dissipating, and feeling very agitated internally. We both agreed it was time to go to urgent care. Saw Dr. at Urgent Care. She offered steroid shot, but stated it would further decrease the effectiveness of the COVID vaccine. Observed that my back was looking better from the hives. Opted to try famotidine and hydroxyzine hcl for allergy and agitation.  2:45 took hydroxyzine and famotidine within an hour, started to have relief from the intensity. That night, I was finally able to  rest and sleep.  Over the next few days, the hives continued to go away, and I wasn't bothered internally by them again.

CUR_ILL: hypothyroid, Gilbert's Syndrome, possible MRSA infection on face

Pharmacist was called into the room to examine patient. ~1 minute later, eyes rolled back in patient's head and she was no longer verbally responsive. Epipen was immediately administered and 911 was called. Pulse was faint but present, breathing was labored, and patient began sweating, Around 1 minute after giving epi, patient was responsive enough to give name, dob, time, etc. She could open her eyes, but was still very dizzy. EMT recommended to go ahead with Benadryl oral dose.. Patient was able to swallow 1 25 mg tablet. EMTs arrived within 5 minutes and took over care; her blood pressure was 80/65 and had  improved to 108/80 right before she left.   The patient told us that she could hear us talking to her the entire time. However, she did not feel the  Epipen injection or realize that she had loss responsiveness. She did agree to go with the EMTs to Medical Center.

Administered vaccine at 12:40pm Pt during administration of vaccine started to pull away but full dose was administered, pt was nervous about the needle. After instructing pt to sit in the post vaccine chair for 15 minutes I noticed visible distress at around 12:50pm. I rushed to her aid and asked her how she was feeling and she reported feeling dizzy. I then helped her out of her chair onto the floor to ensure she would not fall and hit her head - told her to lay supine. I then asked my technician to give me the bp monitor. I then checked her bp and it was below 80/60. I informed her this could be contributing to her dizziness and then asked for consent to help raise her bp. She consented and then I told her I would be lifting her legs in the air to raise her BP. I held her legs in the air for 10 minutes or so and then reassessed her BP and it was 110/48. She started to feel better but reported feeling as if ants were all over her left arm which is where I gave her the vaccine. I assessed once again for angioedema, anaphylaxis, hives, redness, swelling, but didnt see anything. Since the pt was dizzy I did not offer her benadryl liquid but instead offered clairitin. The pt was merely having a panic attack post immunization and said she could swallow tablets and was feeling better. I gave her one clairitn tablet otc. She wanted to sit up so I assisted her to a sitting position while she was on the floor. She sat there for additional ten minutes then moved into a chair and was brought food by her husband because he said she did not have breakfast and thought that could be why she was dizzy. She was not a diabetic so I was not concerned about her BG. She said that this never happened in the past when I reviewed her PCQF form prior to giving her the vaccine. She has had zero history of syncope so this was rare for her. After an additional 10 minutes she had a bp reading of 98/60 and left the store feeling much better

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 11 days after I got the first dose of the Covid19 vaccine, from the manufacturer Modena; I started getting a rash,hives and swelling in my entire body (including my scalp, lips and tongue), these hives got red and swollen, the ones on my face got extremely swollen, I didn't even recognized my self when looking in the mirror because I looked like a different person.  16 days after I got the first dose of the Covid19 vaccine, from the manufacturer Modena; I started getting a red rash/hive on the arm and area where I got the vaccine, I also got this hive/rash on the back of my neck and my upper inner thigh.   I first went to see two different doctors on the 11th day) and by looking at me they told me that this was not something related to the Covid19 vaccine and that it was a mere allergy even though I have never been allergic to anything, one of the Doctors prescribed an anti allergic pills (Fexofenadine 60mg) and the other Doctor did some blood tests to see what I was allergic to ?I?m still awaiting for the results?.  I had to go to an urgent care and saw a third Doctor because even though I was taking the prescribed anti allergic pills, my lips and tongue became very swollen and with a rash/hive on them, and I continued getting the rash on my body. This last and third Doctor I saw, told me by looking at me that this was a reaction to the Covid19 vaccine and that he has seen this same reaction on other patients a day after/several days after getting the Covid19 vaccine. This Doctor prescribed to me Steroids (MethylPREDNISolone tablets, USP 4mg) and asked me to take these for 6 days along with the anti allergic pills I was taking. These helped a lot to reduce the swelling and rash, even though 2 days after the arm got a rash but nothing compare to the days before.
LAB_DATA: Still awaiting for the blood test results.

During the night and the day after (Friday 04/02) symptoms worsened especially heart palpitations being all day above 120  up to 135 per minute. At moments it was difficult to breath and talk. By the end of the day I also experienced chest pain and signs of low oxygen (blue lips and pale colors) as well as mild fever. After calling paramedics, I was transported to the ER where blood, urine  and Covid test were performed. I was told that some values of the blood test could suggest a blood clot so a CTscan was also performed with negative results. After a few hours in observation with infusion of fluids, potassium and magnesium  I was sent home. Saturday and Sunday (days 3 and 4 after the vaccine) symptoms improved however heart palpitations were higher than normal and I still experience mild fever (98-99F). Insomnia and fatigue persisted for two more nights. Finally today Monday April 5, I could say that I feel back to normal.

I am a 25 year old female with no underlying/otherwise known health conditions. I received the vaccine Saturday, March 27th at ~1:30pm. No initial side effects, barely any arm pain, and I felt completely normal and fine for about 8 hours post vaccination. After ~8 hours, I began to develop body aches and tiredness, and within an hour of this onset I got severe chills. A few hours later (this is the middle of the night going into Sunday March 28th) I developed a fever that lasted into the next day. I was not able to take my temperature in the middle of the night but the next morning it had come down to 99.6F (still a slight fever). I had fatigue and tiredness the entire next day. I did not take any medication/fever reducer.  To sum up, I had no side effects upon initially receiving the vaccine, side effects set in ~8 hours post-vaccination and overall lasted about 24 hours. I have had no additional side effects other than those reported and have felt well since those subsided.
LAB_DATA: N/A. Did not seek medical help for these effects.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pt was fine until 15 minutes into her waiting time at which she stated she felt faint and light headed.  Continued to worsen based on dialogue with patient.  Tried to take blood pressure manually as well as with automated cuff but too low to detect.  Pt stated she felt tingly all over, hot , clammy, dizzy and was made worse by opening her eyes.  Put ice packs on neck and forehead as well as wet cloth.  Pt requested water but we declined as to not knowing severity or extent of reaction yet.  Based upon pt not improving and lack of palpable pulse decision to involve EMS was made.  Upon ems arrival 10 min later pt was taken to their transport vehicle for further evaluation.   At that time they observed vitals to be normal, monitored for additional 10-15 minutes and determined pt had adverse reaction, not allergic reaction.  Pts caregiver called us to let us know she was fine on drive home and improved rapidly en route.  Noted pt drove 2-3 hours for appointment, in convertible with temps in mid -upper 70's and noted she was possibly hot upon arrival and this could have precipitated reaction to injection.

It started with my hands getting red and scaly, which at first I passed off as my skin getting irritated from washing my hands at work). Thursday the backs of my hands began breaking out in hive like spots and I started getting itchier skin on my arms, legs, back and stomach. When I got home from work I was breaking out in spots that almost looked like chicken pox (which I had as a child) on my arms, back and stomach, the backs of my hands were rough and bumpy and looked like I'd touched poison ivy, bruise like rashes on my leg. By Friday the hive like spots were spreading down my legs and up my neck to my face, my scalp began breaking out, the skin behind my ears became inflamed and scaly. I had developed every childhood rash I've ever had in a matter of days. I had no fever and otherwise felt fine. I saw a nurse practitioner, but there was no obvious cause for such a sudden flare up of so many different skin reactions at the same time, so she prescribed Prednisone and a topical steroid cream - I have been taking and using both of these since Saturday and the flare ups have subsided and the worst area are drying up and the inflammation is going down. I'm not sure if it is related to the vaccine or not,  but I cannot think of anything that's ever caused such a random flare up all over my body.
CUR_ILL: Allergies, short stomach bug at the beginning of March

SYMPTOM_TEXT: ?Moderna COVID- 19 Vaccine EUA" This is a report of a possible administration error that resulted in "lower-than-authorized dose volume administered (leaked out)."  The patient came to our pharmacy to receive his first dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine during a COVID vaccine clinic day.  He does not normally fill prescriptions at our pharmacy.  The patient weighed above 260lbs, so I chose to use a Safety Needle that was 1 & 1/2 inches in length.  The safety needle and syringe that was used was manufactured by DPS.  The Safety Needle UPC was 6958697604640, Lot 20201110, Exp 2025-11-09.  The DPS 3ml Bare Hypodermic Syringe that was used was UPC 6971352283639, Lot 2010058, Exp 2025-10-09.  The dose was appropriately pulled up in the syringe as 0.5mls.  When I went to inject the patient the needle did not insert into his skin easily, and when I applied extra pressure my thumb must have been on the plunger and a small amount of vaccine discharged from the end of the syringe prior to entering the patient.  A drop of vaccine rolled down the patient's arm for approximately four inches, and the drop was large enough that I did have to wipe it off of his arm following vaccination.  I estimate that the patient did receive definitely half, if not 3/4 of the vaccine dose, as I did have a fair amount in the syringe to push once the needle did break the skin.  One thing that another colleague and I noticed about the syringes is that the plunger slips in and out very easily.  It could be said that it is even too loose.   The needle and syringe were supplied by the state of North Carolina, who we received our vaccine allocation from.
OTHER_MEDS: COVID-19 Vaccine clinic, no medications on file as the vaccine is the only thing that the patient has had at our pharmacy.
HISTORY: Patient may have, but these were not reported by patient for the purposes of obtaining the COVID-19 vaccination.
ALLERGIES: Statins: Cause aches in bones; Bees: Swelling, but no anaphylaxis.
