I continued to use arm normally (I am a swim coach with lots of overhead demonstrations) until I was in acute pain three weeks after vaccine.   At which point I sought care.  Had X-ray and MRI done.  Received oral steroid dose-pack which helped greatly after 3-4 days.  I have started PT to return range of motion and address findings on MRI.  (Rotator cuff and bicep tendon itis)  PT has discovered neck inflammation and loss of motion and is focusing on return of neck motion to start.  She is considering if post-vaccine neck nerve compression is actually the root of my pain.
HISTORY: Anxiety.  Chronic uveitis, fatigue, joint soreness.  Seasonal and household allergies, sometimes lead to wheezing.

When I received my first dose of the Moderna COVID vaccine (Lot # 010M20A) my arm was extremely sore and limited range of motion. I contributed it to just being sore like the literature had sad. When I received my second dose within 20 minutes my arm was extremely sore. It got to the point where I could not lift my arm at all and had no ROM in it at all. It was like my arm just was not working and I would have to move my arm around with my right arm. I was taking 600-800 mg of Motrin every 6 hours and alternating Tylenol 1000 mg and it was not easing the pain. It got to the point where the pain was so unbearable that I went to the Emergency Room on 4/3 where I was diagnosed with Shoulder Injury Related to Vaccine Administration (SIRVA). The gave me some Toradol and Decadron IM and sent me home with Naproxen and Prednisone with orders to follow up with my PCP
LAB_DATA: Emergency room visit on 4/3/21 Follow up doctors appointment on 4/6/21

She got the vaccine, that evening she had a headache.  Then her arm started hurting to the point that she could not move it.  On Thursday, 3/25/21 she was tired but functional.  Then around 5:30 PM she started feeling really strange, odd, felt faint, got hot/cold, her heart was racing.  She laid down as she was at a friends house, they checked her BP, blood sugar and her temperature and they were all normal at that point.  Around 8:00 PM she got the nausea that would not stop and took Zofran.  Around 9:30 she started throwing up.  She then tried Phenergan and was not able to keep that down yesterday.  Then she started running a temperature, and called her doctors office and told her what to look for and to call back if things got worse.  They then got worse, called them back and then around 8:00 AM on Friday they told her to go to the hospital.  When she got to the hospital they started checking things as her fever was higher, her liver enzymes, her thyroid, her kidneys, iron just started going off the page.  Her fever then kept getting higher and higher and at one point it was documented at 104.8, and felt like her organs hurt.  11 days prior to this visit she had just had labs done and everything was normal.  So due to the new findings everything was all elevated, so they checked her for an infection, COVID which was negative, but the intensity of the symptoms got to the point they were unbearable.  She stayed in the hospital for 4 days, and the doctor came in and noted that she had a severe reaction to the vaccine.    They told her to stay longer than the 15 minutes as they had some issues today, and told her that they had to call a medic for 4 other people that passed out, which made her wonder if they had a bad batch or not, and wonders how many people from that day got sick as well.     She still has the most dreadful fatigue, headache and cannot walk from her house to the mailbox without feeling like she is going to faint and used to walking 2-4 miles daily.  Wonders how long is this going to last and that this will pass and that she will be okay, or is she going to be permanently this way.  She feels like she has a bad case of mono or something and cannot stay up and has to go to bed, and also has bouts of insomnia as well.   The body aches are extreme and is taking pain medicine daily due to these symptoms, which she did not have prior to the vaccine.   She got the vaccine, that evening she had a headache. DETAILS OF HOSPITAL STAY: PRESENTING PROBLEM:  Stroke-like symptoms [R29.90] HOSPITAL COURSE:  A 63 y.o. male who presented with chief complaint of left facial droop, left forehead droop and slurred speech.  Patient reports his symptoms started on Saturday and failed to improve.  He contacted his PCP and he was recommended to go to the ER for evaluation.  Patient had his COVID-19 vaccine-1st dose 2 weeks prior and was concerned that he might be having 1 of the rare side effects from the vaccine. On admission patient had normal vitals.  His labs were within normal limits.  Patient's presentation was discussed with Neurology who recommended admission for stroke workup given his comorbidities-hypertension, hyperlipidemia, diabetes and obesity.  Patient received 1 dose of prednisone 80 mg in the emergency department for treatment of Bell's palsy (patient's symptoms more consistent with Bell's palsy presentation).  Patient was admitted to medicine service for workup of stroke with MRI brain without contrast and monitoring for any worsening of neurological symptoms.  Patient's CT head on admission was negative for any acute abnormality.  CTA head and neck showed near occlusion of intracranial left vertebral artery.  MRI brain without contrast was negative for acute infarct.  Patient's facial paralysis slightly improved with 1 dose of 80 mg prednisone.  Patient's presentation was consistent with Bell's palsy.  Patient worked with PT OT and speech therapy and was recommended outpatient physical therapy and speech therapy.  He was discharged home in stable condition on oral prednisone 80 mg daily for 7 days and valacyclovir 1000 mg 3 times a day for 7 days.  Patient was recommended to follow-up with Ophthalmology as outpatient for possible left eye patch if his symptoms fail to improve.  Patient's Lipitor dose was increased to 40 mg daily from 10 mg daily due to finding of atherosclerotic changes on CT head and neck. Active Issues Requiring Follow-up Issue:  Bell's palsy and abnormal finding on CT head and neck. Recommended follow-up provider/specialty:  PCP What is needed: 1. I suffer from tinnitus (ear ringing) originally caused (as best as I can tell) from Aleve and Advil.  It was made worse a few years ago by taking Viagra.  The volume of ringing went up a small amount shortly after taking the medicine, although I attributed that to stress.  However, at roughly the 3-week mark the volume increased dramatically and included pressure in the ear canal.  Imagine the pressure when sitting in an aircraft at takeoff.  The pressure varied over the next day or so but the volume remained at the same high level.  I saw the nurse-practitioner at the doctor's office 2 days later.  He suspects allergies and is not terribly concerned but said I should see the ENT.  I have an appointment with her in early June.    Every other time the volume has tweaked up like this for more than a few hours it has been permanent.  The last time I went for a full hearing test with the ENT (2015) I was told this is a symptom of hearing damage and there is nothing they can do for me.   I am very afraid to take the 2nd shot - the sound is almost at the level of pain.  I'm not sure I can cope with it being much louder, it has gone from being annoying and bothersome to intrusive.  I have canceled my shot #2 appointment for 4/08/21.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: OUR FACILITY HAD CONDUCTED A VACCINE CLINIC ASSOCIATED WITH A PHYSICIAN'S OFFICE ON FRIDAY APRIL 2, 2021. THERE WERE 7 DOSES THAT WERE NOT GIVEN. THEY WERE RETURNED TO THE PHARMACY AND WE WERE TRYING TO MAKE SURE AND NOT WASTE THOSE DOSES. A LOCAL BUSINESS SAID THEY WOULD SEND SOME PEOPLE DOWN TO GET VACCINATED. WE ASKED IF THEY WERE ALL 18. THEY SAID YES. WHEN THE PATIENT CAME IN, I WAS GIVING A VACCINE TO A PATIENT IN THEIR VEHICLE OUTSIDE. I TOLD HIM TO GO INTO THE PHARMACY AND I WOULD BE RIGHT WITH HIM. PATIENT WAS THEN GIVEN THE EUA MODERNA FACT SHEE FOR VACCINE RECIPIENTS AND CAREGIVERS. HE FILLED OUT THE FORM WHILE I WAS FILLING AND CHECKING PRESCRIPTION IN OUR WORKFLOW. I CHECKED THE FACT SHEET AND SAW THAT HE HAD CHECKED YES TO THE QUESTION ABOUT PREVIOUSLY TESTING POSITIVE FOR COVID-19. I COUNSELED HIM ABOUT A POSSIBLE INCREASED IMMUNE RESPONSE TO THE FIRST DOSE OF THE MODERNA VACCINE INCLUDING: CHILLS, MUSCLE ACHES, LOW-GRADE FEVER,ETC.  I DID NOT LOOK AT THE BIRTHDATE BECAUSE I HAD BEEN TOLD HE WAS 18. (THIS  IS WHERE THE ERROR OCCURRED) I PROCEEDED TO VACCINATE THE PATIENT AND ASKED HIM TO WAIT IN HIS VEHICLE OUTSIDE FOR 15 MINUTES TO MAKE SURE HE HAD NO ADVERSE REACTION TO THE VACCINE, WITH INSTRUCTIONS TO CALL US OR HONK HIS HORN IF HE HAD ANY PROBLEMS. THE PATIENT WENT OUTSIDE TO WAIT IN HIS CAR. A TECHNICIAN NOTICED WE HAD FAILED TO GIVE HIM HIS VACCINATION CARD WITH THE RETURN DATE FOR THE SECOND DOSE, SHE TOOK THE CARD TO THE PATIENT AND AS WE THEN BEGAN ENTERING DATA TO OUR COMPUTER AND THE  SYSTEM THE BIRTHDATE WAS NOTICED. THE VACCINE HAD BEEN GIVEN, IT WAS THEN END OF THE BUSINESS DAY. OUR VACCINE COORDINATER CALLED THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH ON MONDAY AM ASKING DIRECTION FROM THERE. WE WERE TOLD TO REPORT TO VAERS. NO ADVERSE EVENT OCCURRED. VACCINE WAS GIVEN IN ERROR. DOH AND CDC RECOMMENDATION IS TO PROCEED WITH 2ND VACCINE.
I received the second Pfizer covid 19 vaccination on Feb 23.  A week later I came down with tinnitus
OTHER_MEDS: Sertraline Latanaprost Timolot Alendronate VitaminD3 Multivitamin

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On March 24 I got the first dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine and I experienced side effects almost immediately. By the time I got to the resting/observation area I felt that the site of the injection got really warm and I became dizzy/lightheaded and started to feel heavy on the chest and little problem in swallowing and breathing. I was taken to the paramedics on site, they checked my blood pressure (which a little high 150/90), oxygenation, pulse, and EKG (which were normal). It did not became too bad after and was allowed to come back home.  However, the heavy chest and swallowing problem lasted for three days. The heaviness in the chested turned into a sensation of feeling like my trachea or the anything under the sternum area was behind strangled. Although I felt like this my breathing and swallowing was almost normal. Every now and then when I swallowed I felt some pain but I could withstand it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 2 minutes after receiving the vaccine, the patient lost consciousness while driving to observation. He continued traveling through the barricades, hit a curb and ran into a light pole and secondarily hit a tree with the back end of his car. He immediately regained consciousness and denied having any head, neck, or back pain. He relayed that he is terrified of needles and shots, and has a history of passing out from receiving shots in the past. He also informed us that he has not had anything to eat or drink since dinner the night before. His vitals were as follows: BP 123/87, HR 104, EKG; Normal Sinus Rhythm. His girlfriend was in the backseat without a seatbelt and she had a hematoma on her forehead. Her vitals were: BP 138/90, HR 98, GCS-15. They both denied transport to the hospital and relayed that they would wait for the tow truck and seek medical evaluation at an urgent care center after.

Received first shot on 3/15/21. On 3/25/21, I developed a rash (hives) around 6:30-7pm. After dinner, around 7:30pm I noticed that my lips were swollen and the rash was spreading. Took one Benadryl and waited 1 hour. Condition worsened so left for ER around 8:45pm. Once there, I was diagnosed with an anaphylatic reaction. I was given Prednisone, Pepcid and Benadryl intervaneously. The Benadryl injection caused my throat to close for a few seconds. Things calmed down so we waited an hour to see if I was responding. There was not a lot of improvement so ER doctor decided to use Epinephrine (EP pen injection). After 2 hours of observation, I was set home to follow up with primary care physcian.
LAB_DATA: None as of yet. We will do the allergy skin test to see if I react once I am off all medications. Currently, I am weaning off Prednisone and taking Zyrtec. Suspected allergens were peanuts, chocolate, soy and ginger. I have never had an allergic reaction to these foods in my lifetime.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 15 seconds of second Pfizer CV19 vaccination, given at appropriate interval from 1st dose, patient experienced cough.  I noted that the patient coughed as she exited the vaccine area to the observation area that was manned by a Registered Nurse.  The RN came to the vaccine area to ask me to help with the patient while she waited in the lobby with another RN.  The patient was sitting in a chair, flushed, distressed, experiencing shortness of breath and repeatedly coughing.  EMS was already called.  I pulled up 0.3mg of epinephrine which was administered IM in the right lateral thigh and 25mg of diphenhydramine 25mg which was administered IM into the upper left deltoid, the opposite arm from the vaccination.  EMS arrived and took the patient to the emergency room approx. 1 mile from the clinic.  She received methylprednisolone 125mg IV, famotidine 20mg IV, and nebulized race-epinephrine upon arrival.  She was discharged home with prescriptions for prednisone 20mg daily x 5 days and an Epipen.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Was fine during the 15 minute observation period. On the drive , approximately 30 minutes after injection I had to clear my throat frequently. This lasted about 2 hours. I did not have any noticeable swelling of my mouth or airway. I was able to breathe fine and did not feel short of breath.  The need to clear my throat eased after a couple of hours and was gone by 5 or 6 hours post injection. At home about an hour after the injection I also noted to my right cheek some pinkness/redness and swelling. It appeared like a possible hive. There was no scratchiness. The redness eased over 12-24 hours, but it was still marginally discolored. The swelling lasted several days and is still present to a lesser degree. I had the expected symptoms of sore arm, fatigue and mild fever (up to 100.9) - none of which were concerning, but the need to clear my throat and the hive were unexpected and thus the reason for the report.

Within 30 seconds of the shot my heart started racing and my throat went into spasms opening and closing.  This went on for over 45 minutes.  The pharmacist said I was nervous and said I was dehydrated which was why and gave me a Benadryl after 45 minutes which after another 25 minutes the symptoms started to slow down, but never stopped.  I had chills and the feeling of ice water in my veins within 10 minutes of the injections.  He kept telling me my signs were common for someone having an adverse reaction.  I eventually drove home and continued on Benadryl.  The next morning when I woke my throat continued closing I called my doctor(pulmonologist) and headed to the ER.  At the ER I received an epi=pen shot, Toradol, Benadryl, Pepcid and Prednisone.   I was monitored and treated for over 4 hours.  Sent home with directions to see my allergist on Monday (was on the meds from ER for 5 days.  Saw the allergist on Monday, 4/5th (the day I finished all the prescribed meds from the hospital) and she has me on Allegra.
LAB_DATA: No medical tests or labs were done at hospital...normal BP was 191/80 and then 159/80 (I'm always 120/80)  Hospital date: 4/1/2021

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the first covid vaccine on 1/4/21 and the 2nd on 1/25/21.  On Feb 22nd I started having heavy vaginal bleeding and severe stomach cramps.  These continued for 9 days and then I went to the Emergency department because I felt like my HGB was low.  They checked it and it was 11.3 and did an abd US that showed my endometrium was thick.  They recommended follow up with GYN and a biopsy.  I continued to have significant bleeding and cramps until the next week when I called the nurse line and they set me up with a virtual visit with GYN provider.  She started me on progesterone and scheduled a hysteroscopy and D & C for the following week.  The progesterone slowed the bleeding down but I continued to experience abd cramps.  I had the D & C and after getting home started to have heavy bleeding and bad cramps again.  The following week I called the GYN provider and she had me come in for another Abd US and checked my HGB which was 9.3.  She also checked for infection and other labs which were all within nml range.  The pathology from my D & C was neg and the GYN really was not worried that is was anything other than a period but was surprised that it was lasting so long.  She gave me TXA and after 5 days on that the bleeding has now stopped but I am still having bad cramps in my lower abd and a lot of bloating.  Also having lots of jolting pains in lower abd.  I have never had  periods that were anything like this and never really had bad cramps like this before.
LAB_DATA: March 3rd 2021 abd US - thickened endometrium March 3rd HGB 11.3 March 24th Hysteroscopy and D & C - pathology negative, cx'd neg March 24th HGB 10.6 April 1st  HGB 9.3, lots of other labs but were all nml April 1st Abd US - normal

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woken up at approximately 3 am with what I can only describe as a back spasm down my entire spine, with what seemed like shoulder blades pulled back.   It did not go away by sitting up or standing.  As I was awake, I went to the bathroom, bringing my phone in case I felt I needed to call 911 while there.  I took an full 325 mg aspirin, and went back to bed, as the aspirin immediately got rid of the spasm/pain.  It could have been due to my recent increase in activity - steps/miles walked (from 1 to up to 4 miles/day).  I have not experienced any subsequent discomforts.  If I had, I would schedule a visit with my primary physician.  I am reporting now as the Nurse who administered my second vaccine shot said I should even though I felt it was not vaccine related. It could be  vaccine related, but it could also be just due to increased activity level. I signed up for v-safe after the incident and didn't attempt to figure out how to report a past event until today, the day after my second vaccine shot.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pfizer COVID Vaccine EUA  Patient received 1st dose of Pfizer vaccine 3/11/21.  3/27/21: Patient is a pleasant 63-year-old female past medical history of anxiety, documented history of hyperlipidemia  came in from outside facility with complaints of dyspnea, COVID-19 pneumonia, bradycardia. Clinical picture started on the 17th patient tested positive for COVID-19 at that time was having symptoms myalgia, subjective dyspnea reportedly went to the emergency department, saturations were good she was discharged home with conservative measures.  At home became more symptomatic and pulse ox was measuring in the low 80s so she went back to the hospital and was admitted to Hospital on 03/25.  Per records patient was started on Eliquis, dexamethasone, azithromycin, remdesivir, p.r.n. Tylenol, p.r.n. Zofran, p.r.n. Toradol along with supplemental oxygen.  Oxygen requirement was 5 L at the facility.  However overnight and prior to arrival providers at outside facility started noticing bradycardia patient's heart rates were dropping into the 30s.  Patient was asymptomatic during these episodes not complaining of any lightheadedness or chest pain.  Reportedly cardiologist saw patient QT and QTC were reportedly appropriate recommended monitoring.  However overnight heart rate continued to go down into the 30s, reportedly on telemetry was noted to be developing Mobitz 2 second-degree block, patient was administered atropine x2 and heart rates improved to the 70s however a year started going down again to 30s and 40s after a couple of hours.  Outside facility requested transfer to another hospital for further management and possible EP intervention.  Bedside patient is lying comfortably in bed currently denies any lightheadedness, dizziness, chills, fevers, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, chest pain, palpitations, paresthesia, swelling of extremities.  Though is she gets winded after exertion, is okay/comfortable on supplemental oxygen at rest.  Patient was increased to 8 L during ambulance ride, was id saturating however medics increased because of bradycardia. Otherwise denies tobacco, recreational drug/marijuana, over-the-counter/herbal medication use.  Social consumption of alcohol will have 1-2 beers a year.  She reports sick contact 1 of her close friends was diagnosed with COVID earlier this month, husband also positive.  She reports she received 1st dose of COVID-19 vaccination around the 10th or 11th of this month 1 day prior to known exposure. Otherwise no medication changes is only on sertraline. Currently no antihypertensive medication or rate-controlling agents.  4/1: Patient was admitted after developing significant bradycardia after receiving remdesivir for COVID-19 pneumonia.  Remdesivir was held and patient received convalescent plasma on 03/28.  Dexamethasone was started at the outside hospital on 03/25.  With also completed 5 days of empiric doxycycline and Rocephin.  Patient CRP and D-dimer were followed and trended down at the time of discharge.  EP Cardiology was consulted and initially the patient was on dopamine for the 1st 2 hospital days.  Was able to be stopped and the last 2 hospital days the patient had no bradycardia.  She will have a Holter monitor as an outpatient.  Patient wore her BiPAP at night.  Oxygen requirements trended down and was able to be on room air at the time of discharge.  Home O2 evaluation was performed and did not require oxygen.  She will continue on 5 further days of Decadron 6 mg daily.  She will follow-up with her PCP.

Presented to ED 3/28/21.  3/28/21: 65-year-old female with past medical history of hypertension, hyperlipidemia, and type 2 diabetes mellitus presented to ER with complaints of shortness of breath. Per patient she received her 1st COVID-19 vaccination last Thursday. Since Monday the patient has felt "unwell." Three days ago she started having shortness of breath which has progressively worsened, especially with exertion. She has developed increased fatigue, cough, nausea and decreased appetite. Denies chest pain. No vomiting or diarrhea. On arrival to ED patient she had a low-grade fever and was hypoxic at 87% on room air. Supplemental oxygen with 2 L NC with improvement in oxygenation saturation to 94%. Laboratory findings were significant for hypokalemia 3.0, transaminitis ALT 55, AST 44. COVID positive. Chest x-ray revealed bilateral airspace disease with obscured pulmonary vasculature. Favored to represent pneumonia over heart failure.  EKG normal sinus rhythm, rate 74, QTC 472. Patient was given IV fluid resuscitation with NS 3 L bolus. Potassium 60 mEq p.o. given.  IV Rocephin was initiated and DuoNeb treatment given in ER.  4/2/21: Pt received remdesivir, convalescent plasma, ceftriaxone, doxycycline, dexamethasone, vitamin C, zinc sulfate. Patient discharged on doxycycline course, PO zinc and vitamin C, supplemental oxygen. Instructed to follow up with PCP in 3-5 days.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 16yo seen for her first dose of the COVID-19 vaccine. She was seated in the back seat of the car. Shortly after receiving her vaccine (within a few minutes), she chose to move to the front passenger seat of the car, and after sitting in the passenger seat she became lightheaded and lost consciousness. Syncopal event was witnessed and lasted a few seconds. She spontaneously regained consciousness, and complained of some lightheadedness and tunnel vision. No significant confusion was noted, her responses to questions were appropriate. Initial pulse was thready and heart rate initially difficult to auscultate. Pale color noted on the face. Initial pulse approximately 50bpm. Breath sounds clear with good air exchange. Patient was placed in a reclined position with feet on the dash.  She quickly recovered and repeat heart rate was auscultated at approximately 70bpm, stronger pulse noted. She was noted to have improvement and she was then driven out of the vaccine site after obtaining consent from her mother (who was the driver) and parked beside EMS. BP was 100/50 and HR 68-72, SaO2 97%.  Lightheadedness resolved and she was feeling well, at her baseline.  She was monitored for 30 min then allowed to leave with her mother, she was at her baseline at last evaluation. Per history review with her mother, she has had 2 prior episodes of syncope with pin removal from hand after surgery and IV placement.

She got her vaccine, and started out with the sore arm, but she was sitting in the bathroom sometime after 11:00 preparing to do a peritoneal dialysis exchange and blacked out.  She grabbed onto the towel bar on the wall and fell hitting her left hip, left ankle and left upper arm.  She does not remember too much after that, but that she was in and out of consciousness until about 12:30 PM Saturday when she remembered being alert but nothing made any sense to her.  Her son came in and found her on the floor, she could not get up, she had a skin tear on her right elbow and she had been incontinent of bowel and bladder.  He started to ask her the orientation questions and got them all wrong, but she knew that she was confused and disoriented.  She could not get up on her own, called the paramedics and they took her to the hospital.  The confusion and disorientation lasted into early Sunday morning 3/28/2021 at about 3:00 AM when she started to answer questions appropriately.  As the day went on things got better, but still exist to this point today 4/6/21.  It was more severe as she came out of the confusion.  She has brain fog, inability to sequence thoughts, a little bit of expressive aphasia.  She had two CAT scans and an MRI that were negative for subdural or CVA's.  I had urine specimen and blood cultures to rule out a UTI or sepsis and those were negative.  Her kidney labs were normal.  She ABG's drawn and those were normal.  They placed her on oxygen and she sat for 3 days and then they released her to home.     Today, she is still having the brain fog, still the not able to sequence thoughts, general fatigue.  She is black and blue from shoulder to elbow due to the fall.
LAB_DATA: She had two CAT scans and an MRI that were negative for subdural or CVA's.  I had urine specimen and blood cultures to rule out a UTI or sepsis and those were negative.  Her kidney labs were normal.  She ABG's drawn and those were normal.

Medications Given in the ED:    4/02 Meds   1:24 p Famotidine 20 mg IV Push; MethylPREDNISolone 125 mg IV Push; DiphenhydrAMINE 25 mg IV Push  1:21 p Albuterol-ipratropium 3 mL Aerosolized 35-year-old female presents for evaluation of allergic reaction following Covid 19 vaccination. Overall she is in no acute respiratory distress. Initially when I walked into the room she did appear anxious, and her voice was a bit hoarse. Lung sounds show subtle wheezing bilaterally. Respiratory at bedside. On further conversation with the patient her voice clarity seemed to improve significantly and she seems to be talking at her baseline. She feels overall that the sensation of throat closure is improving. No other symptoms to suggest acute anaphylaxis and we'll hold on epinephrine administration at this time. Patient was administered IV Benadryl, famotidine, Solu-Medrol in the emergency department.  She was observed for approximately 2 hours after which time she says she is feeling back to baseline. We'll plan to discharge with prescription for EpiPen, and instructions for use discussed with the patient. Also discharged with prescription for burst course prednisone steroids. Return precautions discussed and she was discharged in stable condition.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Starting about 2 1/2 days after the first dose I had aches, significant fatigue, nausea, some subjective fever and slight chills. All of this last 12 days. About 1 week into symptoms also noted some mild shortness of breath and cough. All eventually resolved after 12 days with the nausea being the last symptom to resolve. With the second dose, I felt fine aside from a large red, tender knot on my arm. About 4 weeks later started developing several sizeable pink, indurated areas which did not hurt or itch. the first 3 happened to be in surgical scars- one on right calf, one on left anterior thigh and largest one on right wrist which was 3-4 inches long and felt maybe 1/2-1 inch deep. Then developed similar on right lower eyelid. I did not have a previous scar here. Last to develop was on left upper eyelid and felt shaped more like a BB. At this point, I asked opinion of one of my partners (we are family medicine physicians) and he agreed that it seemed like a reaction to something.  I started taking some ibuprofen for anti-inflammatory symptoms and then took prednisone 20 mg daily for 5 days which did seem to help them resolve, however I still have small palpable areas on right leg and wrist. I have never had an adverse reaction to another medication or vaccine. My vaccines are all current and the last time I was sick enough to miss work was 2004, so I didn't have any other obvious explanation for this.
LAB_DATA: Rapid COVID tests twice in the 12 days after the first vaccine. Both negative. Do not recall dates as done at my own office.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient called the same day as she got her vaccine with us reporting that she believed to have not gotten the full Janssen vaccine. We use circular adhesive bandaids that we vaccinate directly through and patient reported that after having removed the bandaid, "a bunch of liquid ran down her arm". She reported it not being blood and too much to just be some condensation underneath the bandaid. Therefore, she thought it was the vaccine that didnt entirely get into her arm. Unclear how this could have happened, I directed the patient into looking into getting an antibody test in 2 weeks to see if her body produced any post vaccination. She called back two weeks later and said her test came back negative. I called the CDC confused and they reported that antibody tests would not show antibodies produced through vaccination and would only show that produced naturally through previous infection. The CDC then suggested that if there was a device malfunction and that the full dose was not administered, that the dose should be readministered. Patient was adamant that she did not get full dose and after talking to her Dr, it was the pharmacy's decision to revaccinate due to full dose not being administered. We didnt have any Janssen vaccine at that time so we put patient on our waitlist. Patient found vaccine elsewhere and pharmacy readministered there.

Per individual, she stated she woke up a last week and her eye was swollen "almost shut", red, itchy and had "a scaly crust"  She stated she went to the local ER and was prescribed an antibiotic, steroid and antihistamine.  She stated she is not sure why it would do this, but wanted to report it.

Blood pressure 149/98, temp 100.6 complain of feeling feverish and short of breath. EKG was taken which was abnormal and enzymes noted to be elevated. Transferred to main branch of  Clinic approximately 4:30am 4/5/2021. Father states patient has inflammation around the heart.  Had a cardiac catheterization today 4/6/2021-father  states that was normal and patient was started on medication to reduce inflammation around his heart.  Patients father states that patient was very drowsy from his catheterization and was fine with his father telling me the events as they occured.  As I was speaking with patient father, patient was going down for a MRI of the heart. This information was conveyed to me by father and mother. Patient is a college student and was home for Easter break.  Patient currently remains hospitalized in Clinic and father thought he would remain hospitalized until Thursday 4/8/2021 depending on test results and his response to treatment. Both parents state they are willing to be contacted for further information.
HISTORY: Allergies to peanuts, legumes, tree nuts. Last had epinephrine 8 years ago.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient stated she was extremely nervous prior to getting her vaccine. She grabbed her husband's arm to ensure he was close by. He then mentioned that she has a history of passing out and tends to drift off for 15-30 minutes. She would come and go saying she was tired and that she wanted to go to sleep. I repeatedly asked her to open her eyes and tell me her name. The patient did not respond. I checked her breathing which was normal, she was not having any difficulty breathing. I looked for other symptoms of allergic reaction but couldn't find any. This continued for about 20-30 minutes and then the husband stated she has never been in this state for this long. I reached out to my store manager to ask him to call the paramedics. The patient opened her eyes for a few minutes but then would return to her unresponsive state. Patient admitted and diagnosed by dermatology with erythema multiforme (dusky, targetoid appearance with central blister, pale ringe of edema, and peripheral erythematous halo) secondary to herpes labialis. Next, my throat became irritated and I started coughing if I tried to speak. After the irritation subsided I realized that I was breathing more easily too, so I do think my breathing was somewhat affected. Next I felt fatigued, very tired. This was followed by my forehead feeling warm to the touch. My temperature was normal and my heart rate also checked out fine. Then my face turned very red and the skin on my face was puffy. I stopped at a clinic but they had a long line so I went home and took 10 mg of loratadine. The redness on my face and the puffy appearance resolved soon after taking the allergy medicine. All of those symptoms resolved within about an hour and maybe 15 or 20 minutes from getting the shot. The red, puffy skin on my face is what concerned me the most. Nothing in particular was swollen, just the skin looked a bit puffy.
LAB_DATA: None - I took 10 mg loratadine and it seemed to help.

Patient received Johnson&Johnson COVID vaccine in the afternoon on 3/31/21. Patient reported having right arm pain, diaphoresis, chills, nausea, and muscle aches/pain in upper leg/lower back at 5:30am the following morning. Patient took 2 tablets of 500mg naproxen in the morning and in the afternoon. Symptoms did not resolve and patient had to leave work early. Upon getting home patient took 2 tablets of 650mg tylenol and symptoms resolved within 48 hours. On 4/3/21 patient reported mild to severe pain in heel of left foot. The following day the patient went to WellNow urgent care to get his heel examined. During examination provider noticed patient's lesions and patient stated more lesions have appeared since getting the vaccine.  1 on his stomach, 1 on the dorsum of his left foot, 1 on his back, 1 on his left elbow, in between his toes of his left foot, and in between the fingers of his right hand. Patient stated that these lesions cause a burning sensation and can become itchy. Patient was sent to Hopsital ED as provider at urgent care was concerned patient may have purpura. Patient was seen and discharged on 4/4/21 from the ED. The heel pain was determined to be plantar fascitis which was treated with at home exercises with a heel cup. The patient was given clotrimazole for his lesions. The patient had a follow-up visit with his primary care provider at hospital on 4/6/21 in which he explained the clotrimazole only made his lesions worse. Patient was referred to follow up with dermatology on 4/8/21. Primary care provider believes progression of the lesions since getting the vaccine leads to concern of an underlying autoimmune exacerbated by vaccine.
CUR_ILL: No other ilnesses at the time of vaccination or within 1 month of vaccination
HISTORY: Patient has had various lesion on body for past several months (at least 2-3 months)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On second night following the second dose, I experienced racing thoughts and images (not hallucinations) while awakened from sleep. I could not control the thoughts and it felt like what I imagine a bad recreational drug experience would be like. It was frightening because I never experienced anything like it.  It was as if my mind was trying to solve visual word and number problems in flashes. I was drowsy but not asleep. I was sweating but did not have a fever.  I had some nausea but did not vomit.  Over the course of the night, it gradually resolved and felt like a "fever" had broken, even though it was not a fever. I wanted to report it because I have not heard of such cognitive symptoms and there is no other explanation I know of. Prior to this episode after the second shot, I had a variety of  minor headaches, body aches, and chills but nothing significant. I had no symptoms after the first shot.  I woke up exhausted   the following day and am still tired but almost back to normal (third 24 hour period after shot). Thank you for your consideration.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My healthy 18-year old son had his first dose of Pfizer, and within a few minutes he felt dizzy. His heart rate was also rapid. He didn't think much of it, but the dizziness persisted and so they had him lay down with feet up. After about 20 minutes, he began to vigorously shake (rigors I believe is what it is called.) He felt numb in both arms and also his tongue and mouth. We had 3 nurses attending to him, and after about 30 minutes they decided to send him to the ER for evaluation since the very strong shaking and other symptoms were worsening. The shaking, dizziness, numbness all subsided after about an hour. He was given a Zyrtec upon first symptoms about 15 minutes after dose. The ER doc doesn't believe it was an allergic reaction but potentially a strong vasovagal response and immune response. He felt tired after but was completely fine 2 hours later. We were discharged from the ER a few hours later after evaluation. Vitals were in normal range including blood sugar, blood pressure and oxygen. He was fully hydrated prior and had a turkey sandwich and orange prior to coming so was not low on food either. The shaking was very extreme and concerning. It has been almost 24 hours and he is feeling fine other than a sore arm.
LAB_DATA: blood sugar was normal (90) blood pressure was 116/77 heart rate in ER was 83 (but varied between 40's- 80's) Oxygen was 99%-100% Temp was 98.1

about an hour after getting the first vaccine, I started to get hives on the opposite arm. Followed by a itchy sensation inside my nose and sinus areas of face swelling.  I took 50mg Benadryl per pharmacy direction. Reported allergy reaction to my physicians office. At about hour three of the first dose of Benadryl, the symptoms returned. I waited for the four hours between to take 50mg more. The second dose did not change the symptoms but they proceeded to get worse to a sinus headache and back neck/upper shoulder pain. My blood pressure was slightly elevated and I was light headed. I then went to my physicians office urgent care hours. It was confirmed that I was having an allergy reaction to the vaccine and a stronger allergy medication was written. I took Hydroxyzine mg. I did not take a second dose because symptoms were gone in the morning when I woke.
LAB_DATA: 4/5/2021 at 8:05pm I went to Urgent Care, physical examination confirmed an allergic reaction was happening and a stronger allergy dose medication was needed.

RN out to assess pt and again pt was ok sitting but upon standing noted wobbly and asked to sit back down. She did complain of dizziness at this time with some slight shortness of breath. BP noted in 120's with several checks, diastolic BP noted in 70's with heart rate noted 90-110 which per pt elevated HR normal for pt. At this time she did state that she was having some cardiac workup completed and just had  on that was removed on 23rd March. At this time pt was brought back to treatment floor for further evaluation with ambulation assistance by RN. Pt was placed on oxygen 2 liters. BP's remained normal in 120's and HR as well between 90-100. Each time pt felt ok and went to stand she became dizzy and noted wobbly thus asked to sit but BP's remained normal. Pt states she ate some cucumbers and another fruit prior to coming. Pt at 1230 up to restroom with noted vomiting. After vomiting pt stated she was feeling much better. BP noted  124/84 temp 98.1 with c/o of n/v but no other symptoms while in restroom. Left arm noted some patchy redness after pt was itching the arm. At this time pt was given Benadryl 25 mg 2 tablets PO. Continued to monitor pt for about 30 minutes with redness subsiding on her arm, while all vitals remained stable. At this time pt was eager to leave and head home. at 1300 BP noted at 119/73 HR at 100. All symptoms subsided and while pt was standing no wobbling noted. Dr. was phoned and notified of the event as he is the medical director. Pt was given RN number to call when she arrived home.
CUR_ILL: depression, in cardiac work up currently which was not disclosed until after vaccine was given, pt just had a zion monitor which was removed on 23rd March

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The morning of April 3, staff at the Clinic discovered a discrepancy in the preparation of Pfizer vaccine doses. It was discovered that several undiluted vaccine doses were administered. Staff accounted for all unused undiluted vaccine doses. Unfortunately, 10 undiluted vaccine doses had been administered to patients and were not able to be retrieved. This patient received one of the undiluted doses.   The medical team contacted the CDC to determine the potential side effects and observation requirements of receiving an undiluted vaccine. The CDC confirmed that the recipients of the undiluted doses may experience stronger side effects and symptoms than someone who received the diluted dose (sore arm, flu-like symptoms, etc.).  The site public health officer spoke with suspected recipients of the undiluted vaccine to explain potential medical side effects. The Health District will follow up to monitor their status.

20 mins. after receiving the vx (vaccine) I felt some dizziness. Within a few hours of that I felt very tired and developed a sore throat. I also found the slightest exertion left my chest feeling as though someone put a weight on it or the sensation when I can't hold my breath much longer. I was NOT panting for breath or feeling like and asthma attack. I was extremely cold during the night. I went to sleep at 9:30 PM Friday and slept until Saturday 4:00 PM (18.5 hours). I was very achy during that time to the extent that it was painful to be touched.  I felt very weak throughout, as though I had weights attached to my limbs, that entire evening. The dizziness worsened that night to the extent that I felt I might pass out. I still had the sore throat for the entire day. I slept for 10 hours that night (Saturday). I woke Sunday and the dizziness was gone unless I bent over or got up suddenly. The sore throat and achiness were gone. I did have a headache that day. The dizziness returned in the evening and I started to experience nausea as well which made sleeping difficult (Sunday night).  I only slept 3 hours, but other than being tired, I felt that I was getting more energy back and not exhausted like I'd been during the weekend. I had minimal dizziness. I did experience nausea on occasion throughout the afternoon and night. I slept 8 hours Monday night. Tuesday morning  I woke up completely exhausted again. I had a raging headache. As of now (4:20 PM Tuesday) I still have bouts of dizziness. I  have no energy and feel lethargic. I am experiencing a bit of tightness in my chest again when doing minimal exertion.
OTHER_MEDS: Lamictal, Fluticasone Prop spray, Atorvastatin, Duloxetine HCL, Percocet, Levothyroxine, Pregabalin, Hetlioz, Tumeric, Fish Oil, Women's Daily Vitamin,  Hydroxyzine HCL (as needed), Cyclobenzaprine (as needed), Ibuprofen (as needed)

The morning of April 3, staff at the Community Vaccination Clinic discovered a discrepancy in the preparation of Pfizer vaccine doses. It was discovered that several undiluted vaccine doses were administered. Staff accounted for all unused undiluted vaccine doses. Unfortunately, 10 undiluted vaccine doses had been administered to patients and were not able to be retrieved. This patient received one of the undiluted doses.   The medical team contacted the CDC to determine the potential side effects and observation requirements of receiving an undiluted vaccine. The CDC confirmed that the recipients of the undiluted doses may experience stronger side effects and symptoms than someone who received the diluted dose (sore arm, flu-like symptoms, etc.).  The site public health officer spoke with suspected recipients of the undiluted vaccine to explain potential medical side effects. The  Health District will follow up to monitor their status.

Initially (24 hours) I had fever 100.5, chills, aches.  These resolved by 3/20.  Arm was very sore for about 3 days, but took almost a week to completely feel better.     On 3/21 more concerning symptoms started to develop.  Brain fog, spacenesses, trouble looking at books, computer tv.  Very strange sensation.   This resolved by 3/25.     Other symptoms that developed beginning 3/21 were GI upset (diarrhea, stomach churning) as well as insomnia - very short and broken sleep all night with dreams and waking up each time after brief sleep with bad/sour taste in mouth.       The insomnia has gotten progressively worse and unlike anything I've had before.  I do not have a history of insomnia ( I sleep very well) .  For the last week, I do not sleep more than a hour or two at a time and have the broken sleep, with dreams, not a good deep sleep at all, and sour/bad taste in the mouth.  I also don't have  any history of GI problems.  I have been eating a bland diet to try and help with the stomach issues, which have improved somewhat but are still not resolved.     The insomnia is very troubling.    Also occurring is heat sensation in the right hand (this actually developed after my first shot which was 2/23)  that would occur a few times a day where my knuckles are.   In the last several days (starting 4/3)  my right forearm and bicep  have been feeling  of  weakness and numbness, almost like someone has been sitting on it.  Not pins and needles feeling, but weak and numb.  This is somewhat transient, and happens for a few hours each day.  It seems to have improved as of today 4/6.    My physician feels I could have had some kind of neurological response to the vaccine.  I would like to know if this could be the case, or if there is any data showing these symptoms will go away, as I am obviously upset by them.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: **Please note that this form continues the story of diarrhea after my first Covid shot (1/11/2021). See earlier VAERS form for the first incidence.**  I had my second Covid-19 shot on 2/1/2021. The following morning, I awoke with diarrhea, and this continued for nearly three months, with a brief gap from 2/11 to 2/14.  At first, my stool was lumpy, with mucus, but it gradually turned quite watery. It was also clear by eye that I was having trouble digesting higher fiber foods (salads, fruit & vegetable skins, et al.), so I worked to keep to a lower fiber, bland diet. Episodes of diarrhea varied with the day, but they usually occurred first thing in the morning, with some additional episodes during the day or in the middle of the night. By the end of this period, I had lost about eight pounds.
LAB_DATA: Around 3/4/2021, I had a stool test at Hospital that showed the presence of white blood cells (Lactoferrin), but no infection from C. diff, Giardia, Salmonella, Shigella, Campylobacter, and no ova, cysts or parasites.  I finally had a colonoscopy at Hospital on 3/25/2021. A set of biopsies of my colon showed that I had developed microscopic (collagenous) colitis. I began a 10-week tapering course of Budesonide on 3/31/2021. The diarrhea has stopped, and my bowel movements are getting more normal in type and number.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 3-15-21 patient received 1st dose Pfizer vaccine on L deltoid, states that 2 days after the jab she developed a pruriginous rash on ventral aspect of L forearm above wrist area. Rash faded away on its own. Denied SOB, wheezing, cough, facial swelling. denied any rashes on other areas of her body. she did not disclose that rash to us at the clinic. On 04/05/21 she came to the clinic for 2nd jab, on screening and immunization documentation she mark no on "like to speak with health care provider" but prior to HS providing 2nd jab she brought to her attention the previous symptoms. I intervene and discuss with the patient and asked the nature of the previous symptoms. Due to a miscommunication and misunderstanding, on my part, I thought that her rash was initially on site of injection and that it spread distally, discuss with her Covid arm for about 10-15 minutes with patient as I thought initially that it was a COVID arm and proceed to allow 2nd jab and order to keep her in observation for 30'. 2nd jab administered on R arm this time. About 3 minutes after jab, she developed  three lesions on forearm, 2 bumps approximately .2 cm diameter, with mild hyperemia on dorsal aspect of proximal forearm which states were itching. Stated one hyperemic non raised lesion on proximal ventral forearm (that latest lesion was not visualized by me). I extended the observation period and at 45' the lesions started to fade away and the "bumps" got smaller. I did a full evaluation of the patient and there was no other skin lesions on rest of her body. she was breathing normally, no wheezings, no laryngeal stridor, no facial/neck/lips/tongue swelling, no complaints of tingling on lips or tongue. She was not on distress. No treatment provided to patient. Patient was discharge home with specific instructions to call 911, go to neares ER, or call the Duty HS if at any point she develops any new symptoms, breathing problems. Around 6:15 i call patient and told me she was doing good, no new skin lesion, no laboured breathing, wheezing, swelling, problems with swallow and that the lesions were gone. Today 4/6/21 I call patient to come to the clinic for re-assessment and there was no skin rashes, no swelling, her exam was completely normal. she complained of tender arm and that previous night she had some mild headache, took tylenol and better. There was no redness around injection site. Patient was discharged with same recommendations provided previously, to call 911, go to nearest ER, or call Duty HS if any new skin lesions, SOB, wheezing, difficulty swallowing or talking. Just spoke with patient via phone today at 4:25 PM and states she is doing well, no rash, no SOB, completely asymptomatic. I understand the magnitude of these events and I have to say the the misunderstanding was all on me and I take responsibility. Here in our clinic we have immunized over 600 patients and no major issues prior to this. I am available to discuss at any time. Thanks,

Client received his first dose of Covid vaccine in the clinic on 4/1/2021 at approximately 10:25 a.m.  Client was walked to the courtroom for observation for 15 minutes post-vaccination.  This is standard procedure.  When his 15 minutes was up, Nurse informed him that his time was up and he was free to go, and signed him out.  As she was speaking with him, she noticed he was disoriented.  She asked if he was all right and fanned his face for a few seconds. 2nd nurse came by at that time, and the women helped pt. back to the clinic and onto a pad on the floor in a nurse?s office. Third person was called. Vitals were taken several successive times (BP ranged from 148/99 to 155/104), Temp was normal and in 97.5 to 98.4 range.  Resp 16-18. Pulse was between 78 and 93.  Client was disoriented, could not state his name and could not name anyone for us to call.  Ammonia salts were employed with no effect.  All emergency meds, oral airways, and AED were gathered in case they were needed. No other meds or equipment were used. By standard called for the clerk, and By standard, to call paramedics.  She called 911 x 2 and when put through to EMS, was given a disconnect notice.  She ran down the hall to the constable?s offices, who placed the call and had paramedics on their way.  Then two constables (male and an unknown female constable) came to the Health Dept.   Third person got the client to answer with whom to call. Third person called the client?s mother-in-law and employer.  Both arrived after the client was transferred via ambulance and left to join him immediately at the hospital.  As all this was happening, Nurse, 2nd Nurse, third person, and Bystander were attempting to ensure pt. airway and breathing were patent.  He never had difficulty breathing and never had wheezing.  There were no other visible signs of anaphylaxis. His color was pale, then improved, but became pallid again at about the time the paramedics arrived.  He was never alert or oriented throughout the event. Paramedics arrived at approximately 11:00 a.m. They did an initial assessment and received report on what had occurred and data gathered.  They then had to lift pt. onto the stretcher.  He was then transported to Hospital.
OTHER_MEDS: No known medications of any type.
CUR_ILL: No illnesses at the time of vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Admitted 4/3 with a cerebral sinus venous thrombosis, portal vein thrombosis and pulmonary embolus.  Pt received covid vaccine 3/18.  Symptoms began 3/26 which started with chills and body aches. Then on 3/27- developed a severe headache in the back of her head with associated nausea. On 3/28 she had the most severe headache  on the right side of her head. She was vomiting from 3/28-3/30.  On 3/30 she went to the ER for evaluation of her severe headache. She was given a "migraine cocktail", no imaging was completed and she was sent home. Appetite improved on 3/31 and she had a small headache relieved with Excedrin.  Then on 4/1-4/2 she had severe bloating , abdominal pain and fever of 100.4. She had been visiting her mom for the holidays and came to the ER. Imaging revealed  cerebral sinus venous thrombosis, portal vein thrombosis and pulmonary embolus.  She was started on a heparin drip and  brought to ICU for monitoring.. She is not on any oral contraceptives and does not have any family history of clotting disorders.
LAB_DATA: Platelets 124 on admission  heparin-PF4 Antibody 3.018 (positive) because of the heparin-PF4 Antibody 3.018 (positive) and concern for syndrome of thrombosis after covid vaccination she was started on IVIG and switched to Argatroban.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA Fatigue and brain fog starting 24 hours after injection; muscle pain and "grating" shoulder in the arm, "Covid Arm". After about  72 hours the physical symptoms were negligible (other than the Covid Arm rash), but I began having serious trouble with my short term memory. I could not remember things I'd been told or done just a few minutes before - or, rather, I knew I did them, but I could not remember specifics like the name of the food I had ordered or what the actual order was. I could not tell a salesperson in what I needed, what it was called specifically. (Thankfully I had a list to give him.)  I planted a flowerbed and then could not remember what I had planted. Five minutes later I knew I had planted a flower bed, but could not remember which of the two beds it was OR what I'd planted. That sort of thing. I am having hell naming things - if it's got a proper name, I'm really struggling to find it. Nouns. I received the second vaccine on Thursday night and this started on Monday, and today is Tuesday (I think) and it's still going on.
HISTORY: polycystic liver disease Lumbar disc disease

On day of vaccine -- Extreme dizziness  began 1 minute after shot. Dizziness lessened to a tolerable level (I felt I could safely walk around) after about 5 minutes. Dizziness continued to come on sporadically when standing, though lessening in severity and frequency over time. As of today (4/6/21), the dizziness will still occur occasionally when standing or when moving from a sitting to a standing position.  In addition, about 1 hour after the shot, pain began in my jaw and neck area on the left side. This lasted for about three hours. The pain then moved down in my shoulder around the injection site. The pain did not return to my jaw/neck region, and the pain in my shoulder went away after 3 days.  4/2/21 -- Facial and neck numbness began. The left part of my tongue, about one quarter of it, was numb. The left side of my face extending back to my ear and scalp, and down the left side of my neck was numb.  4/3/21 -- Numbness spread down my shoulder, arm, and into my fingers, but was less severe than the numbness in my face and neck.  4/4/21 -- Began 600mg of ibuprofen 3x/day. Numbness decreased after second dose, especially in tongue, but still present. Numbness increased when laying on left side. Weakness in left arm.  4/5/21 -- Increased weakness in left arm and fingers. Numbness still present, but lessened in face and neck. Minor facial swelling in left cheek, left side of tongue tingling and felt slightly swollen. Took 2 Benedryl, did not seem to make a difference.  4/6/21 -- Soreness where left leg connects to hip. Left leg feels a little shaky and weak. Continued symptoms from previous entries. A little brain fog, difficult to concentrate at times. Jaw felt swollen on both left and right side, noticeable when trying to open mouth. Decreased after ibuprofen. Feelings of weakness and general "off" feeling worse when standing versus laying down.
LAB_DATA: 4/6/21 -- Saw a PA at an urgent care. Tested strength, did not find any differences in strength in right versus left sides. Going to see a neurologist tomorrow.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 8 hours after the shot, my joint pain was severe - mostly in joints that I am aware of pretty regularly but the pain was much more intense.  This continued and then at 3:30am I began a fever, headache and the joint pain intensified.  I was barely able to leave bed, and couldn't eat at all, for the next 15 hours - and only then because I took some Tylenol.  Highest temp recorded was only 101.1 but symptoms were horrible.  I had covid in late October, even though two tests were negative Red Cross verified antibodies before my vaccine, and this felt the same but actually intensified even worse.  The fever broke the next night and I woke in a pool of sweat and felt normal for the most part but weak from not eating the entire day before.  So, in total, 36 hours from the time of the shot until the fever "broke" and the joint pain started to subside.
LAB_DATA: I donated blood on March 26th,2021 and they are currently testing for Covid 19 antibodies and on April 4th, 2021 I received a positive result for antibodies.

No position lessened the pain. I thought I had to go to the bathroom twice and felt like I would have explosive diarrhea, but nothing happened either time. I just sat there in pain and sweating. I managed to get a drink of water when I started having this low level feeling that I would throw up and decided not to drink too much. I never threw up either. I laid in bed and went from sweating to freezing and back again. I was seriously considering calling 911, but after about 1.5 hours, the pain went from constant to waves and then I got extremely tired and just fell asleep. The next day I was tired and the fatigue lasted probably 3 days, but I had none of the other symptoms again. My arm hurt from the injection (though I really didn't feel the injection itself) for probably 3-4 days, but I ended up with a bruise for more than a week. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I felt fine immediately after my second vaccine;  about 12 hours later, I woke up due to the most excruciating, electric nerve pain in my right ankle - any of the slightest movement or touch caused this nearly unbearable pain.  It lasted constantly for about 6 hours (I got a little relief from keeping a heated blanket wrapped around my ankle and foot).  The extreme pain finally subsided 6 hours later, and I developed a fever between 99-100 degrees that lasted another 15 hours.  By the following morning, the fever was gone, but I still have remnants of this severe ankle pain that come and go seemingly without cause.  I have not experienced any recent injuries etc that I can associate with this.  The only thing I can think of is when I was 16 years old, this foot was run over by a car and I sustained nerve damage, for which I received extensive physical and nerve therapy that healed the injury.  I have never had any problems with this area, and certainly never this level of pain, until now.  I went to my chiropractor yesterday, but got no relief.  Tomorrow I have a physical therapy appointment;  my chiropractor encouraged me to report this incident

Pt is a 49 YO Female presented with severe anxiety upon initial contact with medical observation physician.  After some coaching and sitting with physician pt decided to get the vaccine and physician gave approval.  Pt then proceeded to booth 9 and a paramedic gave pt her 1st does of the Pfizer vaccine.  Pt was still very anxious but agreed to continue with the vaccine injection. After injection was given pt stayed in booth for an addition 10 minutes with the paramedic.  Pt was coached to take slow deep breathes in order to get her breathing under control.  After pt started to calm down, she was asked if she was ready to proceed to medical observation for her 30 preset time. Pt agreed and we walked to the observation tent.  Pt was transferred to the observation unit team for the next 30 minutes. At approximately 1410, the paramedic was alerted that pt was having an adverse reaction and needed to be medically assessed. The paramedic immediately proceeded to patient with medical equipment given by facility.  Upon assessment pt presented A&OX4, very anxious, skin flushed, complaining of dizzy, lightheaded, and a headache. Pt was speaking normally and vitals were assessed.  Vitals are as follows: At 1418- BP 186/110, HR102, RR26, SPO2 99% Lung sounds clear in all fields, Skins: hot, flushed, moist; At 1427- BP 196/116, HR 99, RR 24, SPO2 98% Lung sounds clear in all fields, Skins hot, flushed, moist. PT was then assessed for possible stroke and was negative slurred speech, negative arm drift, pt had symmetrical smile, and equal grips bilaterally. The decision at that point was made by the paramedic to activate the EMS 911 system for further evaluation and possible ALS ambulance transport to the hospital for further evaluation by emergency physicians. After EMS arrived and assessed the patient, they agreed the patient should be transported to the ER and pt was transported to local hospital, Pt care was transferred to responding paramedics and pt contact ended at that point. Report was given to responding paramedics.
CUR_ILL: Unknown autoimmune disease (Pt stated not diagnosed and that doctors are trying to figure out what is wrong)
HISTORY: Unknown autoimmune disease (Pt stated not diagnosed and that doctors are trying to figure out what is wrong), unknown otherwise

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pt experienced arm numbess immediately after vaccine was administered. the numbness, which was described to travel down the nerve track in her right arm into her fingertips. the pt continued to flex her fingertips, massage the injection site, and rotate arm to lessen the numbness. The pt had diagnosis of contact dermatitis, a delayed reaction from her first moderna dose. it occurred 8 days post vaccine administration (treated with antihistamines and steroids).   the pt also self administered Tylenol 500mg while in the vaccine waiting area. The pt waited in the clinic area for 30 minutes post vaccination, and did not experience any change/worsening of symptoms.  The patient's brother drove her home. I contacted the pt. at 5:09 pm. to follow up with her symptoms. While uncapping a clean needle to administer vaccine, community health worker (CHW) reports that something hit her glove but she didn't think anything of it.  CHW then proceeded to vaccinate patient with same needle without her preceptor's ( Name, NP) knowledge of possible finger stick. Per (Name), NP she also observed CHW push on the plunger before contact with patient's skin and vaccine leaked onto patient's arm. NP feels that  patient received less that half a dose and feels that patient needs to have her dose repeated. After administering vaccine, CHW removed her gloves and realized that she had a small puncture to her left pointer finger. CHW then went to the bathroom, washed her finger, and made her preceptor aware that she had a needle stick. CHW and NP made clinical lead and pod manager aware of incident. Clinical lead observed CHW to have a small puncture wound to her left pointer finger with no blood or fluids visible. Attempted to find patient to make her aware of needle stick with dirty needle, but she had already left clinic. After checking the system and narrowing down patients by vaccinator it was determined that (Name) was correct patient. TC to patient x 2, left message to return call to clinical lead ASAP.  4/6/21- Clinical lead called patient back and she came in to repeat her second dose. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Acute on chronic hypoxia; diarrhea; headache; nausea; This spontaneous case was reported by a pharmacist (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of HYPOXIA (Acute on chronic hypoxia) in an 83-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination.     The patient's past medical history included Ventricular tachycardia, Arteriosclerosis coronary artery, Hypertensive and COVID-19 virus test positive (Hospitalized with mild hypoxemia at that time) in January 2021. Concurrent medical conditions included Latex allergy, Allergy (pregabalin), Weakness generalised, Dementia, Atrial fibrillation, Type 2 diabetes mellitus, Mixed hyperlipidemia, Depressive disorder, Polyneuropathy in diabetes, Peripheral vascular disease NOS and Cognitive impairment. Concomitant products included ACETYLSALICYLIC ACID (ASPIRIN (E.C.)), AMOXICILLIN, FLUOXETINE, FUROSEMIDE (FUROSEMIDE ACCORD [FUROSEMIDE]), GABAPENTIN (GABAPENTIN "PCD"), MEMANTINE HYDROCHLORIDE (MEMANTINE ABDI), METFORMIN, METOPROLOL TARTRATE, PANTOPRAZOLE, POTASSIUM CHLORIDE, ROSUVASTATIN and ZINC OXIDE for an unknown indication.    On 17-Mar-2021, the patient received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 18-Mar-2021, the patient experienced HYPOXIA (Acute on chronic hypoxia) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant). The patient was hospitalized from 18-Mar-2021 to 21-Mar-2021 due to DIARRHOEA, HEADACHE, HYPOXIA and NAUSEA. On 21-Mar-2021, HYPOXIA (Acute on chronic hypoxia) had resolved. Not Provided    DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 18-Mar-2021, Angiogram: chest clear with no pneumonia or pe (Inconclusive) chest clear with no pneumonia or PE. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter considered HYPOXIA (Acute on chronic hypoxia) to be related.    After the patient received the 2nd vaccine dose on 03/17, he became weak and unable to walk. He also experienced headache, nausea, and diarrhea. On 03/18, he was sent to the  emergency department where we received a diagnosis of acute on chronic hypoxia related to the 2nd dose of COVID-19 vaccine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 60 seconds of receiving the injection, I experienced moderate breathing difficulty.   After 10-20 minutes, I noticed that my throat felt slightly swollen (slight difficulty swallowing).  Due to a hyperallergic event that occurred about 12 years ago, I occasionally run into something that triggers the respiratory effect  - although usually the reaction is milder than that caused by the vaccine.  However, the throat swelling is new.  I took a single puff of an Albuterol inhaler around 5 minutes after the injection,  but it had no effect (usually the case for me when the cause is allergic in nature).  About 37 minutes after the injection, medical staff advised me to take an antihistamine.  I took approximately 6 mg of doxylamine succinate (orally).  However, by this point, the breathing had already started to ease slightly.  Approximately 30 minutes later, my breathing was back to normal and the throat inflamation was gone.  It's uncertain how much of that would have occurred through time alone and how much of it was the antihistamine starting to take effect.  My BP was very high when measured during treatment.  Partially explained by the albuterol inhaler combined with pseudoephedrine taken earlier in the day, along with anxiety and exertion from the event itself.
HISTORY: High blood pressure, Type 2 diabetes.  Occasional mild-moderate allergic reactions due to a hyperallergic event from about 12 years ago.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client complained of complained of flushed face, swelling to hands, headache, vision changes and dizziness after receiving Janssen Covid vaccine (lot 1808980 exp 6/20/21). Client was walking out of waiting room and approached the PHN to inform she was not feeling well. Client assisted to closest chair, EMT joined in and started vitals as PHN did assessment. Per client started feeling mild symptoms after 5mins and by 15 mins symptoms had progressed. Client did not alert anyone until her time was done and she began to walk at 1125. Client alert and oriented, flushed face, mild diaphoresis, per client spots in vision, swelling to hands, left hand more, and headache. Client denied shortness of breath, chest pain. History of allergy to penicillin. No other pertinent medical history. Vitals 1125: blood pressure 140/98, pulse 99, oxygen 100%. Client transfered to gravity chair and given water. Client wanted to call husband to come pick her up. 1134: pulse 97, oxygen 98%. Client stated pressure behind eyes. PHN offered client benadryl, flushed face continued, headache, swelling to hands. Client accepted as husband was on his way. Benadryl 50mg PO given at 1137. Vitals 1139: blood pressure 150/90, pulse 95, oxygen 98%. Per client dizzy, felt warm across face, headache, pressure around eyes, swelling on hands and flushed face. Client denied shortness of breath. Client asked if she wanted 911 to be called for further assessment, client denied, she stated she would continue waiting. Vitals 1144:blood pressure 130/90, pulse 97, oxygen 90. Per client headache gone, no flushing, felt tired. 1148 swelling on hands was improving. Vitals 1152: blood pressure 110/80, pulse 89, oxygen 96%. No headache, just pressure on forehead, no flushing, blurry vision improving. Vitals 1157: blood pressure 126/90, pulse 90, oxygen 97%. Per client all symptoms improving. Wanted to sit straight on chair. Client stated felt well enough to go home. Pressure on head was only symptom at this time. Client given ER precautions. Husband was going to driver her home. Last vitals at 1205: blood pressure 120/90, pulse 86, oxygen 97%. Alert and oriented, stood up with no complaints of dizziness. Client walked out of facility with steady gait

On the 9th day (03/28/2021) since the day of receiving the first injection (03/20/2021) I woke up with an itchiness and firmness in the shoulder area of the injection site. Previously, I had no reactions to the shot whatsoever, other than a "bruising" pain the next day following the injection, which healed immediately. By the end of the day, I had a large 6" red rash on the injection site shoulder, that was swollen, firm, hot to the touch and slightly itchy. Reading online that this was a side-effect noted in the Moderna trials, I elected to observe it and not get medical attention for it. I purchased Diphenhydramine HCI 25 mg antihistamine tablets and took two each night, starting on the 29th and through the duration of the rash. The swelling had gone down by the next morning and was completely gone by end of day. I continued to have a rash, firmness, hotness on the area, and a slight itch until 04/02/2021, 6 days later. At this point, the firmness and hotness subsided, but I continued to have a fading rash until 04/04/2021. I experienced no other side-effects or illness. I will be getting my second shot, but in my right arm instead.
OTHER_MEDS: Estarylla Ethinyl Estradol Tablets, USP 0.25 mg (daily pill birth control)
ALLERGIES: Latex that gets into my skin (as in gloves or condoms, and then scratching that area or from friction) causes a very mild itchy redness. I can also get hives on my thighs from walking long distances, but it only happens a couple times a year and I walk 5 miles on the regular so I'm not sure what other factors may also occur in tandem to trigger that (such as heat/sweating/skin irritation).

March 28th - sinus situation the same, diarrhea again, start Pepto Bismol regime based on past microscopic colitis issues  Mucus is thin and clear, just started to discharge.  March 31st - Schedule another appt at Primary Care Clinic due to ?status quo? - this doctor thinks inflammation and prescribes prednisone (2) 20 mg for 5 days  - Covid Test / Strep Test / Influenza Tests = Negative  March 31 - April 4 / Prednisone:  Visibly more stuffed up. Increased tinnitus and increased pressure/burning under my eyes and around my cheekbones.    April 5 - 6 - New symptom appeared approximately a week ago; tightness in throat, difficulty swallowing. I awoke at 6:45 a.m. feeling a bit sore in my arm, but relatively okay.  I was up for approximately ten minutes and then extended my arms over my head to stretch out some of the achiness and immediately regretted the action.  I began to feel dizzy and nauseous and saw black spots encroaching on my peripheral vision.  I washed my face to relieve some discomfort with no change.  I walked toward the bedroom to grab my glass of water when the black spots increased, clouded my entire vision, and I collapsed on the bed.  I then began to hyper-salivate and after waking my husband and catching my breath, I returned to bathroom, experienced diarrhea, and simultaneously vomited into the trash can.  The vomit tasted chemical and extremely acidic.  My body was also shaking uncontrollably during this time and I kept switching between chills and being too hot.  After I felt comfortable leaving the bathroom, I crawled back in bed but was shaking so much that I couldn't stop my teeth from chattering and could not get warm no matter that my husband placed an extra blanket over me.  I had taken my temperature before while I was in the bathroom and it read 94.6 degrees Fahrenheit.  I took it again in bed about twenty minutes later and it read 99.4 degrees Fahrenheit.  My head was splitting and my arm ached, but I was eventually able to go back to sleep.  I felt better after sleeping for a few hours and drinking more fluids.
OTHER_MEDS: Citalopram 40 mg daily Junel Fe (birth control) 1/28
CUR_ILL: Exposed to COVID-19 at week twice two weeks prior to receiving the vaccine.  Experienced daily headaches.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 3/24, I woke up nauseous, extremely fatigued, with sore joints, headache, and abdominal pain.  A few days later I noticed I had extreme shortness of breath.  I went to see my PCP on or about 3/31.  He listened to my heart and discovered a rapid heartbeat.  He then took an EKG.  He wanted to put me on lifetime meds immediately.  I was in shock because I truly believe this is a reaction to the COVID vaccine.  I have never had arrhythmia.  In fact, I had a wellness visit with the Dr. about 3 months previously and all was good.  I have been seeing him for four years since I moved.  He does not think my new diagnosis is related to a vaccine reaction, but I find it highly suspect that 4 other women in my large circle of friends also have AFIB after 2nd shot. I spent Easter in the ER and they pumped Metoprolol in my bloodstream.  I did not stay in the hospital that night.  I went to see the Dr. on Monday morning on 4/4.  He prescribed Metroprolol 25 mg and Xarelto 20 mg IMMEDIATELY.  I picked up the meds and started this regimen.  In speaking with other women, I believe this terrible diagnosis is a direct result as a reaction from the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: April 4th, blood was taken at the medical center.  I was given an EKG and they took a picture of my vital organs

Vaccine Reaction: Nauseated, Syncope and sweating   Description of Event: Pt found in observation chair, sweaty and nauseous and had about a 1 minute syncopal episode observed by OBS RN. Pt slow to arouse post syncope. Able to ambulate 2 steps and placed on gurney. Taken outside of the building by exit doors. Pt sleepy and sweaty, placed on vital sign machine. Dr. and multiple RN's with patient. Pt remained slightly nauseous at 1033. Pt had eaten breakfast and denies any medical history or meds. 1035 attempt sips of water, 1038 we called his girlfriend to come be with him and drive him home. Pt felt like he couldn't get enough air at 1038, we removed both of his masks at this time. Pt was sweaty again, but oxygen sats were 100%. 1056 GF arrived. 1106 we attempt to sit up patient slightly and he gets lightheaded and request to lie flat again. Sips of water causes nausea. Dr. remains at BS with patient. Pt began feeling a whole body tingle, encouraged to take nice slow easy breaths. 1111 took a bite of granola bar.  1143 tried sitting up again, gets lightheaded and laid back down. 1154 Dr. back at bedside. 1200 Pt cold bath blanket put on patient. Pt had periods of being slightly pale during observation period and dry mucuous membranes.Pt refusing to try water or granola bar at this time. 1205 pt began to vomit stomach contents.1212 Dr. back at BS to evaluate patient. Pt feels slightly better, taking sips of water. 1220 pt has been able to lay with head up on his left side now for 20 mins. Dr. offered to send patient to ER to get IVF and be checked out, pt began to perk up and wanted to go home. Orthostatic VS done and remain stable. GF is agreeable to take patient home and monitor him, she is not going in to work today. Pt taken to car via wheelchair, assisted in car, able to walk a few steps. Advised by Dr. to eat a salty meal and drink plenty of fluids and rest. Go to ER if symptoms worsen. Also advised by this RN to follow up with his PCP and let them know of his syncope with vaccine. Pt also advised if he dose get the second vaccine to let them know up front he faints and will be given vaccine in reclining chair.
